turpis. Quisque at lorem interdum risus ornare sollicitudin. Integer in magna ut sapien facilisis interdum. Nulla bibendum arcu ut mauris congue, ac tincidunt ligula dapibus. Nunc rhoncus vitae arcu in sollicitudin.','Dr Pawan Rawal','','publish','closed','closed','','dr-pawan-rawal','','','2019-02-10 16:08:09','2019-02-10 10:38:09','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=doctor&#038;p=10',0,'doctor','',0),(12,1,'2018-03-14 22:03:34','2018-03-14 16:33:34','','Doctors','','publish','closed','closed','','doctors','','','2018-03-14 22:03:34','2018-03-14 16:33:34','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?page_id=12',0,'page','',0),(13,1,'2018-03-14 22:03:34','2018-03-14 16:33:34','','Doctors','','inherit','closed','closed','','12-revision-v1','','','2018-03-14 22:03:34','2018-03-14 16:33:34','',12,'http://hariramhospital.com/2018/03/14/12-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(14,1,'2018-03-14 22:04:33','2018-03-14 16:34:33',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','14','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=14',47,'nav_menu_item','',0),(16,1,'2018-03-14 23:17:42','2018-03-14 17:47:42','','Home','','publish','closed','closed','','home','','','2018-03-14 23:17:42','2018-03-14 17:47:42','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?page_id=16',0,'page','',0),(17,1,'2018-03-14 23:17:42','2018-03-14 17:47:42','','Home','','inherit','closed','closed','','16-revision-v1','','','2018-03-14 23:17:42','2018-03-14 17:47:42','',16,'http://hariramhospital.com/2018/03/14/16-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(18,1,'2018-03-15 01:49:34','2018-03-14 20:19:34','<p><strong>Ambulance Service</strong>: Innovation is the name of the game and our hospital strives for the best of improvements. Our ambulance services have a quality standard that has special trauma care. Our staff is trained to deal with the toughest challenges that come to them. We are geared for all the emergencies including multiple traumas. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We understand that anyone can face an emergency at any moment. The uncertainty of health is a major concern and our Ambulance service is open 24x7. You need to make a call at our helpline number to avail this service if the patients need to be taken. We have a prompt and comfortable Ambulance service that will make sure patient reaches on time without any problems.  </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Features of our Ambulance service-</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Trained personnel and well equipped ambulance.</li>\r\n<li>Effective communication with central room, traffic control and ambulances.</li>\r\n<li>Standard room for emergency that is a part of our network. </li>\r\n<li>Medical and functional procedures across the systems. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The ambulance service will make sure that all the equipment\'s are ready and technologically updated as well. We waste no time in handling a crisis situation and act immediately.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n','Ambulance Service','','publish','closed','closed','','ambulance-service','','','2018-03-15 01:49:34','2018-03-14 20:19:34','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=service&#038;p=18',0,'service','',0),(19,1,'2018-03-15 01:52:20','2018-03-14 20:22:20','<h2>Cardiac Clinic Service</h2>\r\nThere is provision for a cardiac clinic in our hospital where doctors cater to the inpatients. We have cardiovascular consultants that take care of the patients carefully and with full attention. Cardiovascular diseases are one of the highest causes of death. Our goal is to prevent and treat cardiovascular morbidity and mortality rate.\r\n\r\nThe cardiac clinic has all the advanced facilities for check-ups and tests.','Cardiac Clinic Service','','publish','closed','closed','','cardiac-clinic-service','','','2018-03-15 01:52:20','2018-03-14 20:22:20','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=service&#038;p=19',0,'service','',0),(22,1,'2018-03-15 01:54:14','2018-03-14 20:24:14','','Services','','publish','closed','closed','','services','','','2019-02-10 21:14:20','2019-02-10 15:44:20','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?page_id=22',0,'page','',0),(23,1,'2018-03-15 01:54:14','2018-03-14 20:24:14','','Services','','inherit','closed','closed','','22-revision-v1','','','2018-03-15 01:54:14','2018-03-14 20:24:14','',22,'http://hariramhospital.com/2018/03/15/22-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(24,1,'2018-03-15 01:55:01','2018-03-14 20:25:01',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','24','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=24',36,'nav_menu_item','',0),(25,1,'2018-03-15 01:55:01','2018-03-14 20:25:01',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','25','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=25',38,'nav_menu_item','',0),(26,1,'2018-03-15 01:55:01','2018-03-14 20:25:01',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','26','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=26',37,'nav_menu_item','',0),(27,1,'2018-03-15 02:02:31','2018-03-14 20:32:31','<h2>ICU Service</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Intensive Care or Critical Care is a crucial medical field, taking care for patients who are critically unwell. Such patients may need support for ventilator support (airway/respiratory compromise), instability (hyper/hypotension), cardiac arrhythmias, acute renal failure or multiple organ failure, which now widely known as multiple organ dysfunction failure. Patients who need invasive/intensive monitoring, like crucial hours post-surgery, or patients who are unstable to relocate to a less intensive monitored unit may be placed in the ICU.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>The critical care department of our hospital has up to date technology with many specialties. We offer the possibility of a new life for patients who have been severely ill. Our ICU management is based on a methodical group of Critical Care services. It influences general outcome measures like length of stay, mortality and the rate of infection. The 24-hour Intensive Care Units are dedicated to stroke patients, post cardiac surgery, post-transplant surgeries, neonates and paediatric cases. Our hospital has a great medical group of expertise and highest level of development in terms of infrastructure. This makes the services very effective for the care services.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Sufficient emphasis is placed on areas such as standardizing care through clinical ways, nurse training and determining the ethical and economic issues relating to Critical Care making our hospital one of the finest indeed.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Some of the key features to look out for-</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>ICU Management:</strong> Infection Control is of our prime importance. Protocols for infection control relate to a huge range of interventions. It is jointly developed with anaesthetists and intensivists. Checklist of intricate care is done on a daily basis. Prolonged stay in the hospital owing to significant illness of the patient is addressed due to high risk of infections associated with it. Infection control policies like hand wash before and after checking the patient; alcohol hand rubs; sterile disposable gloves and barriers; safe throwaways of patient consumables and all things sharp; bedside analysis checklist, i.e, improved infection control guides. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Clinical transferences:</strong> Standardized clinical handovers are ethically done here. A great deal of care is given for the transfer of physicians to physicians or nurse to nurse, in case of any change in location or change in shifts. Clinical transferences also include important information like patient care, verbal order, test results, treatment and services, present condition, current or any anticipated changes that take place within the patients. Transfers of duties are done by informing the relatives of patients, if needed. The physicians and nurses are well trained to handle the handovers.</p>','ICU Service','','publish','closed','closed','','icu-service','','','2018-03-15 02:02:31','2018-03-14 20:32:31','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=service&#038;p=27',0,'service','',0),(30,1,'2018-03-22 19:45:22','2018-03-22 14:15:22','<h2>Gynaecology Clinic Service</h2>\r\nThe gynaecology department of our hospital has a great number of facilities and understanding professionals. It deals with high risk, complicated deliveries and pregnancies that are referred from other nursing homes and private hospitals. We have special procedures to deal with the reopening of the fallopian tube blocks, ovarian cancer, etc. Our hospital has well equipped neonatal unit. This helps to take care of the premature and low weight babies. Our gynaecology department has blood bank that serves round the clock for any emergencies that occur. We also look into cases like large uterine fibroids.\r\n<h3>Facilities and procedures-</h3>\r\n<h3>Hysteroscopy â€“ Diagnostic:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Identification of Uterine cancer</li>\r\n 	<li>Post-menopausal bleeding</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Laproscopy- diagnostics:</h3>\r\nProblems like Abdominal pain, Infertility work up, identification of primary amenorrhea, analysis and management of ectopic pregnancy are done here.\r\n<h3>Laproscopy- operative:</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Tubectomy</li>\r\n 	<li>Myomectomies</li>\r\n 	<li>Laparoscopic Ovarian Cystectomies</li>\r\n 	<li>Laparoscopic assisted vaginal</li>\r\n 	<li>Adhesiolysis</li>\r\n 	<li>Oophorectomies hysterectomy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Other complications-</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Cervical dysplasia-</strong> It is a condition where abnormal changes happen in the cell of the cervix. If itâ€™s left untreated, it may lead to cervical cancer. Routine gynaecological and PAP smear is done to find out about Cervical dysplasia. Generally an HPV infection causes the changes and growth in the cells. Both HPV and Cervical Dysplasia do not have any specific symptoms but the treatment depends upon the changes in the cervixâ€™s cell.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Endometriosis-</strong> A number of women complain of pelvic pain for years. Later, they are often diagnosed with endometriosis. To minimize pain, traditional treatment goes to remove the ovaries. At our hospital, we try minimally invasive solution to take care of such matters and aim to save the ovaries. The cause for such condition is still unclear but hormonal changes and hereditary factors are taken into account.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Menstrual disorders-</strong> There are different types of menstrual problems that all women deal with. Some of them include heavy periods, missed or irregular periods and Dysmenorrhoea (painful periods). Our physicians will do individualized treatment for any problem a patient suffers. There may take a surgical treatment or interventional radiology procedures, depending on the case.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Pelvic floor disorder-</strong> Those suffering from pelvic floor disorders may experience urinary problems like painful urination, incomplete emptying of the bladder, straining or constipation, urgent need to urinate, pain or pressure in the rectum or vagina. Our compassionate team of qualified professional help improve such conditions through their wide range of hands on training. With all the knowledge, innovative treatments, advanced technology and personalized plans for each patients creates optimal health. We treat prolapse conditions, bowel dysfunction, bladder dysfunction and other pelvic floor disorders.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>HIV and womenâ€™s health-</strong> Women who are infected with HIV have unique needs in terms of reproductive health. Our team has the required expertise in both HIV and AIDS. AIDS is a major leading cause of death today. Special needs like Obstetrical care, HIV counselling, community outreach, antiretroviral therapies are available. Services under HIV program include routine Pap smear, annual gynaecology exam, genital tract infection treatment, analysis and treatment of vaginal bleeding, management of gynaecologic problems, preconception and family planning care, peer counselling and the right to HIV testing for partners.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Sexual health-</strong> Couples come for treatment of sexual health and its related symptoms quite frequently. We treat them with utmost confidentiality and great respect. Some of the issues couples or women may go through, but not limited to, are cases like vaginal dryness, loss of libido, uncomfortable and painful intercourse and depression. Treatments may include hormonal and non-hormonal therapies and therapies with trained psychologists or psychiatrists who have expert knowledge in sexual health.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Ovarian cysts-</strong> An ovarian cyst is a sac with fluid that forms on the ovaries. It is a very common and benign in most of the cases. They vary in sizes and often disappear on its own. Some cases require surgical removal. In very rare cases, the cyst twists or ruptures that causes serious complications. Symptoms of ovarian cysts include mild abdominal pain, pain during sexual intercourse, irregular menstruation, unusual hair growth on face, etc.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nMany other problems are also taken care of in our hospital. The patient just needs to make prior appointment with us.','Gynaecology Clinic Service','','publish','closed','closed','','gynaecology-clinic-service','','','2018-03-22 19:45:22','2018-03-22 14:15:22','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=service&#038;p=30',0,'service','',0),(31,1,'2018-03-22 19:46:50','2018-03-22 14:16:50','<h2>Medical Check-up Service</h2>\r\n<strong>Why go for health check-ups?</strong>\r\nToday, we have a very stressful and unhealthy lifestyle. The routine life of every person has changed sharply since the past 10 years. People are more prone to diseases and ailments because of the hectic days. The population has increased rates of diabetes; osteoporosis and even life-threatening diseases like cancer are on the rise. For these reasons, we provide regular medical check-up.\r\n<h3>There are many reasons that a person should go for health check-ups. Hereâ€™s why we encourage them-</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Early diagnosis of a problem</li>\r\n 	<li>Regular check-ups for better health</li>\r\n 	<li>Medical check-up packages for different age groups</li>\r\n 	<li>Proper follow up of any illness identified</li>\r\n 	<li>Customized packages for larger groups of people</li>\r\n 	<li>Organized and systematic procedures to keep it a hassle free process</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Here are the following packages:</h4>\r\n<strong>(Insert packages)</strong>\r\n<h5>Preparation for the check-up:</h5>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>The entire check-up can take a couple of hours.</li>\r\n 	<li>Wear loose clothes and removable footwear.</li>\r\n 	<li>Certain tests may need 12 hours of fasting, please consult and come.</li>\r\n 	<li>Samples of stool and urine may be needed for certain packages. Please bring it in a dry and clean container. One can take a sterilized container from our clinic as well.</li>\r\n 	<li>In case of on-going medications of the patient, they will be requested to bring them along for checking. Any kind of discomfort in the patient will be assisted to.</li>\r\n 	<li>Smokers should not smoke on the day of the check-up</li>\r\n 	<li>Patients are required to abstain from alcohol, 24-hours prior to check-up.</li>\r\n 	<li>Ladies are advised not to undergo check-up during their menstrual cycle</li>\r\n 	<li>Diabetic patients should not take insulin on the day of the check-up.</li>\r\n 	<li>Patients can bring earlier records of medical check-up (2-3 years).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nThe healthcare and medical needs are of utmost importance. We take care of patients, from the beginning of life to adulthood. Immediate assistance and access to all the facilities are done without wasting much of patientâ€™s time. Our medical check-up facilities are very modern and standardized. We believe in keeping the relationship between the patient and doctor very open for excellent health care. There is a passion to excel in the field of medical care and patient queries. Our staff will serve the patients suitably to avoid wastage of time.\r\n\r\n<strong>NOTE- </strong>Please note that patients, who have high blood pressure, are diabetic, are pregnant or have any other medical complaint should inform the staff beforehand.','Medical Check up Service','','publish','closed','closed','','medical-check-up-service','','','2018-03-22 19:46:50','2018-03-22 14:16:50','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=service&#038;p=31',0,'service','',0),(32,1,'2018-03-22 19:47:17','2018-03-22 14:17:17','<h2>Ophthalmology Clinic Service</h2>\r\nOphthalmology clinic of our hospital has all the facilities and experts who can treat various different kinds of problems related to the eye. It can range from a simple routine eye test to many other conditions of the eye. The expertise is not limited to just the eye but also its surrounding areas as well. The team that we have ensures that everything is examined thoroughly from start to end. Therapeutic equipments are available for treating problems like cataract, glaucoma, external and corneal diseases, paediatric ophthalmic diseases, aesthetics and other disorders.\r\n<h3>Medical procedures-</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li><strong>Eye exam-<strong> A series of tests are done to examine the eye. Any complaints related to it on the early stages are checked thoroughly before coming into a quick conclusion. Various kinds of instruments are used to determine the quality of vision and check for eye disorder. A bright light may be shone directly on the patientâ€™s eye and request them to look into range of lenses. Different tests and evaluation are done to know different aspects of the vision of the eye and its health. Generally, people who start having regular headaches and see changes in the focus of vision must go for an eye check-up as there are chances of near or farsightedness.</strong></strong></li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Cataract surgery-</strong> It is process where the lens of oneâ€™s eyes are removed and, in most cases, substituted with another, artificial lens. This surgery is done to remove the haziness or clouding in the lens which is normally clear. The cataract surgery is done by a professional eye doctor, an ophthalmologist, on the basis of outpatient service. This means that a patient does not have to stay overnight in the hospital after the surgery. Cataract surgery is a very common and a very safe procedure. The doctors do a follow up round after the surgery just to check if everything is fine.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Cornea transplant-</strong> Cornea transplant, also known as keratiplasty, is an intricate surgical procedure where a part of a patientâ€™s cornea is substituted with a corneal tissue from an anonymous donor. Cornea is essentially a dome shaped, transparent surface of the eye that is the reason for an eyes focusing power. For the restoration of a personâ€™s vision, improved appearance and reduced pain or diseased cornea, cornea transplant. Most of the transplant is highly successful. Some of the transplant procedure may have a risk of cornea rejection of the donor. These cases are looked upon on another level.</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Lasik Eye surgery-</strong> This is procedure where the eyes are corrected for its vision problems. For people who want to eliminate or reduce the need of possessing of eyeglasses or lenses can go for this surgery. Lasik eye surgery is a very common kind of refractive operation. Such surgeries change the shape of the transparent dome shaped tissue (the cornea) at the front of the eye. The wanted result of Lasik surgery is to refract or bend light rays to emphasize more precisely on the retina rather than at one point short or beyond of the retina. The aim is to create a sharper clearer vision through this delicate surgery.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAll of these procedures are done in a fine manner. The doctors have an open discussion about all the pros and cons of surgery.','Ophthalmology Clinic Service','','publish','closed','closed','','ophthalmology-clinic-service','','','2018-03-22 19:47:17','2018-03-22 14:17:17','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=service&#038;p=32',0,'service','',0),(33,1,'2018-03-22 19:48:07','2018-03-22 14:18:07','<h3>Outdoor Visit Service</h3>\r\nMany a timeâ€™s patients visit a hospital for minor illness. They do not need to be admitted unless the doctor really thinks so. For such purposes, we have the Outdoor Visit area. The facilities in this part of the hospital are inclusive of blood tests, X-rays, ECG, plaster, minor surgery, MTP, physiotherapy, injection, immunization, etc.\r\n\r\nThe Outdoor visitors can avail the wheelchair/trolley service if needed. The patients are called again in another date so that further investigation is done in some cases. This can be done out of turn as well depending on the situation of the case.\r\n<h4>Our outdoor visit section has the following facilities-</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Separate car park</li>\r\n 	<li>Snacks and coffee shop</li>\r\n 	<li>Waiting room</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPatients may have to wait for a long time in order to get a check up hence a waiting room is provided for them. Each patient is looked upon for general problems that take minimum time. A follow up is considered by the doctor if required.','Outdoor Visit Service','','publish','closed','closed','','outdoor-visit-service','','','2018-03-22 19:48:07','2018-03-22 14:18:07','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=service&#038;p=33',0,'service','',0),(34,1,'2018-03-27 18:07:37','2018-03-27 12:37:37','<h2>Outpatient Rehabilitation Service</h2>\r\n \r\n<p>Outpatient services are those where the patients are not kept overnight for any major procedures. This is a service that is done on a daily, weekly or monthly basis depending on every patientâ€™s case. We offer different kinds of rehabilitative therapies to different to different individuals. The team of qualified and efficient doctors help create a better living for patients in need. Our programs include maximum function and well-being of individuals and make their living better qualitatively. In short, our mission is to help people get back to the real world as fast as possible after a trauma, injury or illness.</p> \r\n\r\n<h3>Services and programs- </h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n\r\n <li><strong>Physical therapy-</strong> Non-surgical treatment for the joints and muscles. Specific training is given to people who need muscle strength and functional movement. This is done to promote healing, lessen the pain and regain normal function. Scientific studies and evidence-based studies of therapies have shown improvements in patients. Problems of lower back, fractures, tendonitis, arthritis, knee pain, neck pain, chronic headache, joint inflammation, ligament/muscle/tendon tear, sprains and strains, post-op rehabilitation are offered at our hospital.</li>\r\n \r\n<li><strong>Speech therapy-</strong> Many individuals suffer from problems of cognition, language, communication, swallowing or voice. In such cases, we have speech therapists who help regain these functions or help one adapt with such conditions.  Some of the disorders that occur through and diagnosed plus treated here are brain tumour, stroke, brain injury, neck/head cancer or neurological conditions such as Dementia, multiple sclerosis, ALS or Parkinsonâ€™s disease. We practice many kinds of therapies as per the conditions. </li>\r\n \r\n<li><strong>Occupational therapy-</strong> When a person has suffered from an injury, it takes him/her time to recover. Their daily life routines like work, cooking, hobbies, personal hygiene, shopping are hampered. To get back to normalcy, occupational therapies are done. Adjusting with the environment is important and our team helps you do it. Promoting independence on an emotional level is our motto. Treatments include dexterity training, ergonomic evaluation, cognitive rehabilitation,, vision therapy, therapeutic exercise, handwriting training, training for home management, adaptive technology training, ADL or self-care training. We all want to live a life full of productivity and maximum energy and we aim to do so for our patients. </li>\r\n \r\n<li><strong>Individual health (men and women)</strong> - Physical and emotional needs are very important at any age of life. Special needs are given to individuals on a therapeutic, behavioural and holistic level. We have created a health and wellness program for both men and women for each phase of life so that they do not have to worry about an abdominal, pelvic pain, chronic disease or any chronic pain. Our licensed therapist helps to give a patient a comfortable and soothing environment. Some of our approach include respecting each other as individuals, respecting your belief and religion, providing care for an all-round physical health, etc. One can expect sharp decrease in pain through proper evaluation, techniques, instruction and suggestions accordingly. </li>\r\n \r\n <li><strong>Cognitive Behavioural therapy-</strong> Many of us go through stress on a daily basis. Some can cope with it in their own way, others canâ€™t. They may go through anxiety and depression of different level. Different types of tests are done to know the person and a therapy course is made for them accordingly. This helps the mind to be healthier, rational and positive than before. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The patients go through a tough period mentally and rehabilitation may take time. If the doctors and patient work together for a goal and are motivated enough, the process may be quicker. It is important for the patient to open up and speak about their problem which is crucial for their recovery. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Outpatient Rehabilitation Service','','publish','closed','closed','','outpatient-rehabilitation-service','','','2018-03-27 18:07:37','2018-03-27 12:37:37','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=service&#038;p=34',0,'service','',0),(37,1,'2018-03-27 18:10:41','2018-03-27 12:40:41','<h2>Outpatient Surgery Service<h2> \r\n\r\n<p>The outpatient surgery services are available in our hospital. The patients who undergo surgeries that do not need overnight stay come under outpatient surgery department. The concept of this department is to have one-time cost (save the cost of overnight stay). This service has been rise in demand and hence we cater to it without any difference in the quality. Due to the smaller medical procedure and zero bed requirements for the night, the charges are much lower. But despite this fact, all the procedures are given equal importance. The surgeries are done in a very intricate way no matter how small the procedure. We ensure that the patient comes for a follow up in order to have proper recovery.</p> \r\n\r\n<p> Some of the procedures that are available here are Excision of the cyst, circumcision, diagnostic cystoscopy, colonoscopy etc.</p> ','Outpatient Surgery Service','','publish','closed','closed','','outpatient-surgery-service','','','2018-03-27 18:10:41','2018-03-27 12:40:41','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=service&#038;p=37',0,'service','',0),(38,1,'2018-03-27 18:11:37','2018-03-27 12:41:37','<h3>Pathology Lab Service<h3> \r\n\r\n<p>Our hospital staff is quite dedicated towards their work. They work diligently in all the services without any difference in the quality. Our pathology laboratory services have provided some of the finest facilities to the medical community. Because of this, we have earned a distinguished reputation of superiority, leadership and integrity. The commitment towards the service that we deliver will never go down and will continue to give exceptional results.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The pathology department adheres to the norms of quality control programme. The maintenance of all the equipments is under the contract issued by the manufacturer. Every device is regularly calibrated according to the standards of the government rules. This guarantees reliability and accuracy of all the tests done.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4>There are different other sections that come under the pathology department-<h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Histopathology-</strong> Our experienced pathologists use well equipped automated tissue processor, cryostat, embedding station. The services include histopathological reporting, frozen sections histopathological reporting and immunohistochemistry.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Hematology-</strong> An expert group of team for identification and cure of blood diseases. The haematologists analyse and treat the patients with many types of conditions like anaemia, reduced or increased white blood cells, decrease or increase in platelets; bleeding or clotting disorders, inflamed lymph nodes or spleen. Our department of knowledgeable doctors also intend to cure blood cancer including problems like lymphoma, leukaemia, multiple myeloma and other kinds of diseases and disorders as well.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Serology-</strong> A serology laboratory is for analyzing the blood for any diseases that can affect the publicâ€™s health significantly. The measurement and detection of antibodies are done in this lab through a serology blood test. If people are exposed to antigens, i.e, viruses or bacteria, their immune system creates particular antibodies against the foreign organism. These antibody levels are checked to determine if the infection took place recently or a long time ago. Our clinic conducts tests for blood-borne pathogens. This includes Hepatitis B, HIV and diseases that are risk to the general public. Tissue specimens of animal suspects are also taken for an investigation if an outbreak occurs.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Biochemistry-</strong> The biochemistry laboratory has various test menus serving various clinical specialities. The tests have top quality standards that for an all-around patient care. We have electrolyte analyser, clinical chemistry auto-analyser, semi -automated analyser, immunoassay analyser which is based on Electro Chemiluminescence and many more. All the equipments are connected to the management of the hospital so that quick results take place and all information is well updated. We also have the research work done in the laboratory on biomarkers in different diseases.</li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Cytopathology-</strong> The diagnosis and study of diseases on a cellular level comes under the branch of pathology. Here, the study of free tissue fragments or cells are studied intricately. The identification of cancer and diagnosis of infectious diseases and inflammatory conditions are done here. Pap smear, a screening device to discover pre-cancerous cervical lesions, is used to know about cervical cancer. We have two methods to do the smear tests- Exfoliative cytology and Intervention cytology.</li> \r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Microbiology-</strong> The microbiology department is fully equipped with computerized systems that involve blood culture, tuberculosis culture, susceptibility, sensitivity and bacterial identification. Facilities for the analysis of rare microbes are also done in our laboratory.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','Pathology Lab Service','','publish','closed','closed','','pathology-lab-service','','','2018-03-27 18:11:37','2018-03-27 12:41:37','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=service&#038;p=38',0,'service','',0),(39,1,'2018-03-27 18:12:50','2018-03-27 12:42:50',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','39','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=39',39,'nav_menu_item','',0),(40,1,'2018-03-27 18:12:50','2018-03-27 12:42:50',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','40','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=40',40,'nav_menu_item','',0),(41,1,'2018-03-27 18:12:50','2018-03-27 12:42:50',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','41','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=41',41,'nav_menu_item','',0),(42,1,'2018-03-27 18:12:50','2018-03-27 12:42:50',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','42','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=42',42,'nav_menu_item','',0),(43,1,'2018-03-27 18:12:50','2018-03-27 12:42:50',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','43','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=43',43,'nav_menu_item','',0),(44,1,'2018-03-27 18:12:50','2018-03-27 12:42:50',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','44','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=44',44,'nav_menu_item','',0),(45,1,'2018-03-27 18:12:50','2018-03-27 12:42:50',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','45','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=45',45,'nav_menu_item','',0),(46,1,'2018-03-27 18:12:50','2018-03-27 12:42:50',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','46','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=46',46,'nav_menu_item','',0),(47,1,'2018-03-27 18:15:46','2018-03-27 12:45:46','<h2>Anaesthesia and Pain Management</h2>\r\nAnaesthesia is a kind of medicine that is given to patients who undergo surgeries. It creates a loss of awareness and sensation in a patient so that the patient does not feel any kind of pain. To let the intolerable pain go away, this drug is used.\r\n<h3>There are 3 kinds of Anaesthesia-</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>General- This one is a form of Anaesthesia where the person loses all consciousness. The activities of central nervous system are suppressed.</li>\r\n 	<li>Local or regional Anaesthesia- This is given on the part of the body where operation is required. There is a loss of sensation in that part only. The consciousness of the person is otherwise intact.</li>\r\n 	<li>Sedation- The central nervous system is less conscious under sedation. The degree varies from the general Anaesthesia. The anxiety and long-term memories are inhibited with remaining conscious.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Pain management techniques include-</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Interventional procedures</li>\r\n 	<li>Referral to other medical specialists</li>\r\n 	<li>Medication management</li>\r\n 	<li>Psychological counselling and support</li>\r\n 	<li>Acupuncture and other alternative therapies</li>\r\n 	<li>Physical chiropractic therapy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAll of the skills depend on the degree of pain and area. Our experts know exactly what treatment is suitable for each case. A history is taken and detailed analysis is done about the pain, gravity of it, duration, disturbance in daily life and many more. Sometimes ultrasound or MRI scan is needed to know about the pain in depth.\r\n<h3>Types of pain-</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Neuropathic pain- These are pain that is caused by disease or damage that affects the CNS (central nervous system). Pains that donâ€™t have any obvious source or occur suddenly come under this category.</li>\r\n 	<li>Nociceptive pain- these are caused through cuts, sprains, tissue damage, fractures or any injury that indicates the peripheral nerves to the brain.\r\nTreatments for pain vary from case to case. Some may just need medicine whereas other may need therapy and medicine or combination of both. Steroids are the last or only option for some. Some patients are given antidepressants to help increase the amount of serotonin.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nOur doctors help improve the quality of the patient life so that they can lead a normal life. Pain management essentially aims to eliminate the pain on a long term basis to erasing it fully. Detailed discussion with other discipline of doctors is also possible for advice and treatment methods. We have all the technology to support the patients. Pain can cause a lot of distress to a person mentally too and hence we have psychologists to help them out.','Anaesthesia and Pain Management','','publish','closed','closed','','anaesthesia-and-pain-management','','','2018-03-27 18:15:46','2018-03-27 12:45:46','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=47',0,'department','',0),(48,1,'2018-03-27 18:17:28','2018-03-27 12:47:28','','Departments','','publish','closed','closed','','departments','','','2018-03-27 18:17:28','2018-03-27 12:47:28','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?page_id=48',0,'page','',0),(49,1,'2018-03-27 18:17:28','2018-03-27 12:47:28','','Departments','','inherit','closed','closed','','48-revision-v1','','','2018-03-27 18:17:28','2018-03-27 12:47:28','',48,'http://hariramhospital.com/2018/03/27/48-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(50,1,'2018-03-27 18:18:23','2018-03-27 12:48:23',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','50','','','2018-04-02 23:25:33','2018-04-02 17:55:33','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=50',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(52,1,'2018-03-27 18:29:50','2018-03-27 12:59:50','<h2>Bariatric Surgery and Weight Reduction </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Each and every day, there are new cases coming up about weight issues. People are either overweight or underweight. Obesity is rising in huge a degree that is affecting the quality of health of many. If the body isnâ€™t fit, it affects the mind as well. Hence, depression is on the rise due to body image issues. \r\nFor these reasons and many more, our hospital provides facilities of weight reduction and bariatric surgery. A thorough examination and assessment is done and only then a decision is made by our doctors. Relatives of the patient need to be present for such decisions.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Bariatric surgery</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>People who are suffering from obesity undergo the variety of procedures that come under Bariatric surgery. It is a type of weight loss surgery that is possible through shrinking the size of the stomach. This is done through a gastric band or by removing a portion of the stomach or by resecting and redirecting the small intestine towards a small stomach pouch (a gastric bypass surgery). </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Past studies and detailed long-term studies have shown that such procedures cause significant long-lasting loss of weight. It has also shown the recovery from another most common disease called Diabetes and has improved the cardiovascular health risk factors. Weight loss surgeries have significantly reduced the mortality rate 40% to nearly 23%. According to the U.S National Institute of Health, a recommendation of bariatric surgery is done only when the Body Mass Index of a minimum of 40. For people who have a Body Mass Index of 35 and have some serious medical condition that coexists with the weight issue can be advised for such a surgery too. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Different reports and updated norms suggest that bariatric surgery is also possible for people who have a BMI of 35-40 without any other health conditions or a BMI of 30-35 with severe health conditions are accepted. The most recent guidelines suggests that people who have a BMI of more than 30 with severe comorbiditiesis a major candidate for bariatric surgery.</p> \r\n\r\n<h3>Types of surgical procedures-</h3>\r\n\r\n<strong>Blocking procedure</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Biliopancreatic diversion</li>\r\n<li>Jejunoileal bypass</li>\r\n<li>Endoluminal sleeve</li></ul>\r\n<strong>Restrictive procedure</strong>\r\n<ul><li>Adjustable gastric band</li>\r\n<li>Vertical banded gastroplasty</li>\r\n<li>Sleeve gastrectomy</li>\r\n<li>Stomach folding</li>\r\n<li>Intragastric balloon (gastric balloon)</li></ul>\r\n<strong> Mixed procedures</strong>\r\n<ul><li>Gastric bypass surgery</li>\r\n<li>Implantable gastric stimulation</li>\r\n<li>Sleeve gastrectomy with duodenal switch</li></ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The doctors in our hospital are highly trained for all the procedures and have indigenous skills to treat a patient. They have all the knowledge and are willing to discuss the matter openly to ensure safety measures pre and post-operation. After any kind of procedure or recommendations, follow ups are done by our professionals. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Bariatric Surgery and Weight Reduction','','publish','closed','closed','','bariatric-surgery-and-weight-reduction','','','2018-03-27 18:29:50','2018-03-27 12:59:50','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=52',0,'department','',0),(54,1,'2018-03-27 18:30:56','2018-03-27 13:00:56','<h2>Cancer Surgery and Chemotherapy </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Cancer is a disease that is caused by uncontrolled growth of cells in the body. It is not a singular disease. It is a group of disease that displays a common feature (cell growth). Cancer can happen at any age but it increase with age. The study of cancer is called Oncology. It includes the diagnosis, cure, and treatment of it. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Benign Tumour and Malignant Tumour-</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Sometimes tumours are non-cancerous in nature. They are called benign tumours that do not spread or metastasize in the body. They do not have the tendency to invade or destroy any other tissue or cells adjacent to it nor do they migrate to another location via blood or lymph. \r\nA malignant tumour on the other hand is cancerous in nature. They damage the adjacent tissues or cells and even organs. This can be life threatening for many. If the cells break from the main tumour and make their home in another organ such as the liver or kidney, this results in a new tumour site. This is called secondary tumour or metastasis.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Causes of Cancer-</h3> \r\n\r\n<p>Almost all the cancers are caused due to defects in the genetic material of the call that has transformed. These defects or abnormalities can be due to carcinogens. Carcinogen is present in smoke, radiation, chemicals, tobacco or any infectious agents. Other reasons that can promote cancer can be due to errors in DNA replication or may have been inherited and hence present in all cells right from the birth.</p> \r\n\r\n<h3>Treatment- </h3>\r\n\r\n<p>It is a common misconception that cancer is incurable. Different methods are effective in curing it according to the condition of the person. Many are cured and more can be cured if it is detected in the early stages and the treatment done promptly. We aim to cure the affected persons with the best cancer treatments and save lives. In some cases, cure is not a promise however the treatments is aimed at controlling the disease from spreading and make the patients feel comfortable for as long as possible.   Each diagnosis and treatment is designed according to an individualâ€™s age, stage of cancer and the type of cancer they have. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>We have five kinds of excellent treatments-</strong> Surgery, radiation therapy, chemotherapy, and immunotherapy and hormone therapy. The goal of surgeries and radiotherapy is to eliminate the disease from its main site of the cancer. Chemotherapy, immunotherapy and hormone therapy deal with the cancer that may have spread outside the primary site of the cancer.</p> \r\n\r\n<p><strong>Surgery-</strong> this the most important part of the treatment for this disease. It attempts to eliminate the cancer cells by removing the tumour. Some areas of the tissue surrounding may also be removed as it may contain the cancer cells. The process is simple safe and very affective way when the cancer is tiny and restricted to the site of origin. Surgeries are best for certain types of cancer such as head and neck, breast cancer, early lung and cervix cancer and other gastrointestinal or skin cancers. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Chemotherapy-</strong> this method uses drugs that cause problems with the growth and cell divisions of malignant nature. Once a patient takes these drugs, it circulates throughout the body and so this is much better and highly beneficial for managing the cancer that spreads in the whole body like lymphomas, leukaemia and testicular cancer. Fundamentally, the treatment of this disease is multidisciplinary. The combination of radiation, surgery, chemotherapy in particular sequence depending on the stage and site of the cancer. </p>\r\n\r\n<h4>The patients are kept in the loop and are given the best diagnostic services. Our imaging services include</h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fluroscopy</li>\r\n  <li>Mammography</li>\r\n  <li>MRI scan</li>\r\n <li>SPECT-CT Scan</li>\r\n <li>Ultrasonography with Color Doppler</li> \r\n <li>Conventional Radiography </li>\r\n<li>SPECT-CT Scan</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>All of these facilities are available with skilled and qualified staff. They cover the most comprehensive task intricately from start to end. </p>\r\n\r\n','Cancer Surgery and Chemotherapy','','publish','closed','closed','','cancer-surgery-and-chemotherapy','','','2018-03-27 18:30:56','2018-03-27 13:00:56','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=54',0,'department','',0),(56,1,'2018-03-27 18:31:52','2018-03-27 13:01:52','<p><strong>Cardiology and catheterization lab:</strong> Cardiology is a branch under the medical world which deals with heart related disorders and the circulatory system. The diagnosis and treatment of congenital heart diseases, heart failures, coronary artery diseases, electrophysiology and valvular heart diseases are done under Cardiology department. We have experienced cardiologists, cardiothoracic surgeons to assist patients with in-depth and great care. We also have diagnostic services such as echo cardiology, angioplasty, cardiogeriatrics, and interventional cardiology andpediatric cardiology.\r\nOur facilities include modern techniques of medical tools and procedures.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Cardiothoracic CCU-</strong>The CCU has well equipped bedside Doppler, nurses round the clock, echocardiography system, infusion pumps, constant oxygen supply, ventilators, defibrillators, pressure monitoring systems, intra-aortic balloon pump, temporary pace maker, electrolyte analysis machine.</li>\r\n	\r\n<li><strong>Non-invasive cardiology-</strong>This department is supervised by senior experienced cardiologists. They are very dedicated in their field. Some of the procedures that take place are vascular dopplers, stress echoes, oesophageal echoes, dobutamine stress echoes, foetal echoes and intra-operative TEE.</li>\r\n	\r\n<li><strong>Electrophysiology- </strong>For the evaluation of cardiac arrhythmias and to understand their mechanisms, electrophysiological studies are done. There are facilities for patients of dilated cardiomyopathy and heart failure via multi-site pacing. The patients are examined by an EP study. There are also provided with ICD (implantable cardioverter defibrillator). If required. ICD acts as a life saving device.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n<h4> Cath Lab-</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We have progressive catheterization laboratory in our hospital. Patients are examined in this room with diagnostic imagining tools used to carefully visualize the arteries of the heart and its chambers. Our doctors and staff take individual care of patients. Any abnormalities or stenosis found in a patient is taken care of in this room. The staff for the Cath lab has team of doctors who have multiple knowledge in this field. The team is well trained to come to a quick solution of a topic or a problem. This multidisciplinary team will take the finest steps to ensure that the patients are diagnosed properly. A cath lab may consist of cardiac physiologist, nurses and radiographer.</p>\r\n\r\n<h5>A number of procedures are performed in this lab like-</h5>\r\n\r\n<ul> \r\n<li>Coronary angiography</li>\r\n<li> Angioplasty</li>\r\n<li>Percutaneous Coronary Intervention</li>\r\n<li> Balloon Septostomy</li>\r\n<li>Transcatheter Aortic Valve Replacement</li>\r\n<li> Catheter Ablation</li>\r\n<li> Pacemaker fittings</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n','Cardiology and catheterization lab','','publish','closed','closed','','cardiology-and-catheterization-lab','','','2018-03-27 18:31:52','2018-03-27 13:01:52','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=56',0,'department','',0),(57,1,'2018-03-27 18:32:43','2018-03-27 13:02:43','<h2>Cardiology Department </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The cardiology department of our hospital is supremely equipped with all that one needs. The team has experts of faculty in cardiovascular medicine, transplant cardiology, cardiac arrest, advanced cardiology, structural intervention, electrophysiology, cardiac imaging, resuscitation sciences, etc. The team is committed to giving advanced patient care and are willing to stay updated with every new knowledge that come their way. The cutting edge research and egalitarian approach to cardiovascular disease is highly commendable.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>We have the best operation theatre, cath lab, cardiac step down ward, beds for modular ITU, ICCU, CTVS ICU, ambulances for comfortable transference.</p>\r\n \r\n<h3>Procedures and surgeries that are done here â€“</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Open heart surgery</li>\r\n	<li>Closed heart surgery</li>\r\n	<li>Minimally invasive cardiac surgery (MICS)</li>\r\n	<li>Congenital heart diseases and valvular corrections</li>\r\n	<li>Vascular surgeries and grafting</li>\r\n	<li>All kinds of thoracic surgeries</li>\r\n	<li>Coronary angiogram </li>\r\n	<li>Peripheral Angiogram, Angioplasty</li>\r\n	<li>Total Arterial grafting for CABG</li>\r\n	<li>Stenting of arteries</li>\r\n	<li>Embolotherapy for visceral bleeding </li>\r\n	<li>Beating heart surgery (off pump)</li> \r\n	<li>Re-do cardiac surgery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Post-surgical follow-ups:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Holter</li>\r\n	<li>Ecocardiograph</li>\r\n	<li>Collection of blood sample from home</li>\r\n	<li>Physical medicines and support for rehabilitation</li>\r\n	<li>Cardiac CT scan to assess the recovery progress</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Our procedures and surgeries are affordable and thoroughly updated according to the norms. The patient has no need to worry as all their doubts are discussed including all the pros and cons of every service. Our patient are our duty and their wellness our priority of the highest degree. </p>\r\n\r\n','Cardiology Department','','publish','closed','closed','','cardiology-department','','','2018-03-27 18:32:43','2018-03-27 13:02:43','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=57',0,'department','',0),(58,1,'2018-03-27 18:33:19','2018-03-27 13:03:19','<h3>Chest and Respiratory Medicine</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Physicians for chest and respiratory check-up care for patients who are going through problems of lung disease, asthma, emphysema, cancer, COPD (chronic obstructive pulmonary disease) and many other respiratory disorders. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our hospital has facilities for such check-ups that include a broad range of specialist services like ECG, CT Scan, urine and blood test, Lung function tests, spirometry. This enables the doctors to analyse and treat the patientâ€™s complaints accordingly.</p> \r\n\r\n<h4>Some of the major chest and respiratory problems are- </h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Sarcoidosis</li>\r\n  <li>Sleep disordered breathing</li>\r\n  <li>Interstitial Lung Disease</li>\r\n <li>Allergy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','Chest and Respiratory Medicine','','publish','closed','closed','','chest-and-respiratory-medicine','','','2018-03-27 18:33:19','2018-03-27 13:03:19','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=58',0,'department','',0),(59,1,'2018-03-27 18:34:00','2018-03-27 13:04:00','<h2>Dental Department </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Dental problems arise in every 1 of 2 people nowadays. Today, a rising awareness is needed on proper dental care. At our dental department, there are all the necessary tools required for any procedure a patient needs to go through. Our chambers are completely sterile and we aim to give our patients a stress free experience. Dentists aim to give you what you really need rather than just selling the services. Our hospital abides by giving their clients the correct advice. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The services available at our hospital are as follows- </h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Root canal treatment (RCT) - </strong>This kind of treatment takes place because a personâ€™s tooth is infected. To protect it from decontamination from a microbial attack a sequence of RCT is done. A number of sittings are required depending on the case. Various steps involve such a treatment. Our dentists would guide you with each step.</li>\r\n	\r\n<li><strong>Bleaching/whitening-</strong> Many people cannot live a full life because they do not smile openly. Teeth whitening can help those who suffer from tooth discolouration or other problems. Teeth whitening can be done in this department which is not at all painful. </li>\r\n<li><strong>PFM crown and bridges-</strong> If a tooth is damaged decayed or cracked, crowning needs to be fitted on it. It is a permanent covering that is put on top of the original tooth. It can be of metal, gold, porcelain or acrylic resins. Crowns are fitted to shape. </li>\r\n<li><strong>Extraction- </strong>A tooth extraction is the process of removing the tooth from its roots. Reasons for such a procedure are many such as the tooth blocking another tooth for growth, to remove the baby teeth that do not fall naturally, to create space for readjustment of other teeth after putting braces, infected tooth, wisdom teeth if they cause problems of any kind. The extraction can be done either simply or through surgery. </li>\r\n<li><strong>Dental implants- </strong>A surgery that involves metal frames or posts that are positioned onto the jawbones, beneath the gums. Once this is done, the replacement tooth is put on it. Implants are done because, for some, ordinary dentures and bridges arenâ€™t suitable. In order to do such procedure, one needs to have healthy gums and healthy bones to support it. </li>\r\n<li><strong>Polishing and scaling-</strong> Dental cleaning consists of the removal of the tartar and plaques deposits. This process helps the teeth look good and smooth. It also letâ€™s your teeth stay hygienic. </li>\r\n<li><strong>Tooth jewellery-</strong> According to the latest trend, tooth jewellery is becoming high on demand. Many youngsters use this as an accessory to brighten up their smiles. \r\nMany other problems are catered to and will be addressed as the patient comes to our hospital. Your smile makes a difference and we will make sure that you receive the best from our side. </li>\r\n\r\n</ul>\r\n','Dental Department','','publish','closed','closed','','dental-department','','','2018-03-27 18:34:00','2018-03-27 13:04:00','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=59',0,'department','',0),(60,1,'2018-03-27 18:34:36','2018-03-27 13:04:36','<h2>Diabetic Clinic</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Today, diabetes has become a very common phenomenon amongst even the youth. It occurs because of the pancreas does not secrete enough insulin. As it goes low, the more a person is susceptible to diabetes. It may also happen if the cells produced in the body do not respond appropriately to the insulin. This kind of disease happens in 3 main forms- Type 1, Type 2 and gestational diabetes. Most of them have high sugar level due to over eating of sweets, high cholesterol, obesity and genetics. People who suffer from diabetes have to cut down on sweets or have medicines.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>General precautions include a healthy diet, normal body weight, exercise and avoiding tobacco. Diabetes doubles the risk of a personâ€™s death. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Signs and symptoms of diabetes- </h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Weight loss (for Type 1 and Type 2)</li>\r\n<li>Increased thirst (polydipsia)</li>\r\n<li>Increased urination (polyurea)</li>\r\n<li>Increased hunger (polyphagia)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The symptoms may develop within weeks or months for Type 1. Whereas in Type 2, it takes a longer time and happens subtly. Low blood sugar is a very common symptom in both Type 1 and Type 2 diabetes. Other symptoms apart from the above include headache, blurry vision, slow healing of cuts, fatigue, and itchiness. Skin rashes may occur in diabetes which is called diabetic dermadromes. Under emergencies affects can stat from sweating, feeling of unease, increased appetite, trembling, confusion, unconsciousness, seizure, brain damage and even death. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>How to reduce glucose consumption?</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>All one needs a genuine determination to practice healthy eating. A proper dietary practice will help regulate balance in the body. Some of your goals should be- </p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Avoid junk food</li>\r\n<li>Consume carbohydrates</li>\r\n<li>Have frequent but small meals</li>\r\n<li>Avoid saturated fats at all cost</li>\r\n<li>3 servings of permissible fruits everyday</li>\r\n<li>3 servings of fish everyday</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Hypoglycemia can occur and can be mistaken for drunkenness. Severe cases need special treatment like injection with glucagon or intravenous glucose. Diabetic ketoacidosis is a condition where the patient experiences metabolic disturbances that consist of nausea, abdominal pain, vomiting and breathing problems. \r\nOur hospital has facilities for diabetes check up and treatment. Today, patients can check their sugar level on their own with digital machines in seconds. This gives them an idea about their sugar control on a daily or monthly basis as prescribed by doctor. It is easily available in markets and reliable too. However the tool should be used after a consultation with the doctor at least once. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Diabetic Clinic','','publish','closed','closed','','diabetic-clinic','','','2018-03-27 18:34:36','2018-03-27 13:04:36','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=60',0,'department','',0),(61,1,'2018-03-27 18:35:08','2018-03-27 13:05:08','<h2>Emergency and Trauma Centre</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The uncertainty regarding a personâ€™s health is always high. Due to this reason, our hospital has a hassle free and swift emergency facility. Since emergency and trauma needs quick, cutting edge procedures and fast decision making skills, our hospital provides just that.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>A team of cardiologists, neurologists, trauma specialists, neurosurgeons are present 24x7 for all the medical emergencies. Their years of experience make them the best in their field and are of great value when time becomes precious. Updated medical assistance including the emergency vehicle is available at the hospital. Our goal is to focus on the patient who needs major focus at the time of trauma and emergency. The doctors and nurses are fully trained for any situation that arises any time. Our staff also know the emergency evacuation techniques if needed.</p> \r\n\r\n<h3>What we treat?</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Fatal accidents</li>\r\n<li>Victims of natural disasters</li>\r\n<li>Strokes</li>\r\n<li>Heart attack</li>\r\n<li>Poisioning/suicide cases</li>\r\n<li>Polytrauma</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We also have the best psychologist/psychiatrist for such patients as trauma can have PTSD (post-traumatic stress disorder). Our hospital even has an air ambulance service for cases that need immediate focus without wasting any time on traffic. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have mobile ventilator, infusion pump, ECG machine, Defibrillator, portable CT scan, Fibro-optic lights, pulse oxymeter, portable echo machine and ultra sound machine. These technologies make it far more efficient to diagnose a person during emergency period. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Some of the features of our centre- </h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Door to triage situation takes place within or lesser than 5 minutes. </li>\r\n<li>Access to doctors within 5 minutes</li>\r\n<li>Time taken from door to cath lab is quite fast. </li>\r\n<li>Experts in the emergency care always present. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Our hospital has systematic protocol approach to every situation that comes to us. The process for the emergency unit is scientifically developed and protocol driven. We have standardized rooms for the patient with common efficient and medical protocols.</p> \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Emergency and Trauma Centre','','publish','closed','closed','','emergency-and-trauma-centre','','','2018-03-27 18:35:08','2018-03-27 13:05:08','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=61',0,'department','',0),(62,1,'2018-03-27 18:35:37','2018-03-27 13:05:37','<h2>Endoscopy and Colonoscopy </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Our hospital conducts endoscopy procedure with the finest people around the patient. It is a process where the gastro-intestinal tract is seen through a flexible, lighted tube that has a camera attached to it at the end. Sample of tissue cells (biopsy) in small quantity is also taken, in some cases, for testing.  </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>We conduct two main types of endoscopy-</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Colonoscopy- </strong>The lining of the colon, rectum and the large intestine can be viewed by a bendable tube which is inserted through the rectum. To undergo this test, a person must only drink clear liquids 24 hours prior to the test. The doctor gives a medicine or laxative to clear the bowel from stool. </li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Upper endoscopy- </strong>To get a clear picture of the esophagus, small intestine and stomach, a flexible tube is inserted through the mouth. To undergo this test, the patient is not supposed to eat or drink 6 hours prior to the appointment. A clear stomach will help give a safe and better view. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Colonoscopy is not a painful process as it seems. There will be pressure, cramping or bloating during the procedure. A sedative is given to help patient stay relaxed and create a tolerable process. The whole process takes around 40 to 60 minutes excluding the waiting, preparation and recovery time.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>During upper endoscopy, the personâ€™s throat is sprayed with a local anaesthesia. The endoscope is then used to view the esophagus, stomach and duodenum. This process does not disturb the breathing of the patient. Many patients fall asleep during the process and others find it slightly uncomfortable. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Endoscopy has its set of risks too. There can be chest pain, damage of organs, swelling or redness or persistent pain in the endoscopic region. Dark coloured stool, difficulty in swallowing and vomiting after the colonoscopy can indicate that something is wrong and immediate action needs to be taken. </p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Other types of endoscopy- </h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Bronchoscopy- To examine the lungs</li>\r\n<li>Laproscopy- To examine the pelvic or abdominal area</li>\r\n<li>Hysteroscopy- To examine the uterus</li>\r\n<li>Cytoscopy- To examine the bladder</li>\r\n<li>Laryngoscopy- To examine the larynx or voice box</li>\r\n<li>Uteroscopy- To examine the uterus</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>All the procedures are done very carefully under proper vigilance. The technology is up-to-date for the best treatment. A patient must inform the doctor about their medications, allergies before the procedure. A proper discussion between both the parties is done with patientâ€™s consent to perform the procedure. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Endoscopy and Colonoscopy','','publish','closed','closed','','endoscopy-and-colonoscopy','','','2018-03-27 18:35:37','2018-03-27 13:05:37','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=62',0,'department','',0),(63,1,'2018-03-27 18:36:10','2018-03-27 13:06:10','<h2>ENT</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Almost every person suffers problems related to ear, nose, throat, head and neck. Problems and diseases in the base of the skull for benign tumour or cancer are also looked upon. \r\nA group of the finest qualified doctors and highly advanced technology available makes for a great treatment and we believe in that. The department of E.N.T (ear, nose and throat) are equipped with just that. We give care to patients who have problems regarding ear, nose and throat, of all age groups. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Treatments- </h3>\r\n\r\n<h4>Ear Treatments (surgeries):</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Tympanoplasty</li>\r\n<li>Stapedectomy</li>\r\n<li>Mastoidectomy</li></ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Head and neck surgery:</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Thyroid</li>\r\n<li>Parotid surgery</li>\r\n<li>Submandibular</li>\r\n<li>Surgical oncology</li>\r\n<li>Endocrine surgery</li>\r\n<li>Microvascular reconstruction</li>\r\n<li>Endoscopic surgery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Otology</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Ear</li>\r\n<li>Hearing</li>\r\n<li>Balance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Facial Corrective Surgery</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Scar revision</li>\r\n<li>Spot and removal</li>\r\n<li>Cosmetic surgery</li>\r\n<li>Rejuvenation surgery</li>\r\n<li>Maxillofacial surgery</li>\r\n<li>Craniofacial surgery</li>\r\n<li>Traumatic reconstruction</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4>Cochlear Implant</h4>\r\n<h4>Audiology Room</h4>\r\n<h4>Endoscopic Sinus surgery</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Rhinoplasty</li>\r\n<li>Septoplasty</li>\r\n<li>Sinusistis</li>\r\n<li>Anterior skull base</li></ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Other procedures- </h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Voice surgery</li>\r\n<li>Phono-surgery</li>\r\n<li>Swallowing disorder</li>\r\n<li>Nasal surgery</li>\r\n<li>Sleeping disorder treatment</li>\r\n<li>Snoring correction</li>\r\n<li>Apnea</li>\r\n<li>Tonsillectomy</li>\r\n<li>Adenoidectomy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4>Facilities under the ENT department-</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>All the facilities at our hospital are available with updated tools and machines. All the treatments are done with close collaborations with the specialties of neurosurgery, neurology, radiology, pulmonology, allergy, internal medicine, radiotherapy, immunology and oncology. They are well updated with the latest medicines and norms given by the government. \r\nThe ear, nose, throat department has the most number of problems as well. Treatments for sinusitis, bronchitis, tonsil removal and other general problems are also looked at. </p>\r\n\r\n','ENT','','publish','closed','closed','','ent','','','2018-03-27 18:36:10','2018-03-27 13:06:10','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=63',0,'department','',0),(64,1,'2018-03-27 18:36:49','2018-03-27 13:06:49','<h2>Hair Transplant </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Hair loss is quite a common reason in todayâ€™s day. The reasons can vary from physical health problems (injury or diseases), mental stress, or environmental causes. The reason why hair transplant is done can be a very personal choice for every person. The common purpose of hair transplant is to look better than before, but is not limited to that. Some reasons can be to improve the hair density, correcting the hairline or baldness restoration. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hair transplant can be for the eyebrows, eyelash, skull hair, etc. The surgeons at our hospital will leave no stone unturned to make your wish come true. An open communication will be present where our qualified doctors will give their patients an overall picture of the procedure, its pros and cons as well.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>A hair transplant is the only long lasting, permanent way to restore the hair. It comprises of hair transplantation of the hair follicles in its naturally arising sets. When a transplant is done, it is taken in account that the hair on the occipital lobe is never lost. The most important thing is that they use it when they are relocated to the required site or the recipient site. Such procedures are done under the meticulous process of local anaesthesia. The duration of the whole procedure can vary between 6-10 hours depending on the quantity of grafts transplanted. Once the surgery is done, the transplanted hair starts growing within 8-10 weeks.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Follicular Unit Extraction (FUE)- </h3>\r\n\r\n<p>FUE is used for the rebuilding of hair for lowering the position of the frontal hairline, correcting the previous punch grafting, beard and moustache transplant, etc. After a few days post treatment, patients can use shampoo on their scalp normally. The normal activities are advised from the very next day of the treatment. Doctors advise not to do any such workouts or strenuous exercises that may create pressure on the scalp. This should be followed for at least 3 weeks. The downsides of post-ops are always discussed with the patient but they are next to negligible. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>( Please note that everything is done before a proper consultation, analysis of the scalp and other examination with senior doctors. There may be cases where doctors do not recommend such procedures due to various reasons.)</strong> </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Hair Transplant','','publish','closed','closed','','hair-transplant','','','2018-03-27 18:36:49','2018-03-27 13:06:49','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=64',0,'department','',0),(65,1,'2018-03-27 18:37:22','2018-03-27 13:07:22','<h2>In Vitro Fertilization</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Many couples or women face numerous issues related to pregnancy. Various solutions work for different couples. Some approaches may only apply for women depending on the case. IVF or In Vitro fertilization is one of them. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>There are times when couples find it difficult to conceive and there can be many reasons for it. In Vitro Fertilization is a unique way to have a baby. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Understanding IVF-</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>To know about IVF in a better way, it is important to understand the natural and spontaneous process of conception. In between a menstrual cycle, an egg is discharged from the ovary inside the fallopian tube. The fertilization takes place in the fallopian tube where the egg stays for many days. It divides and becomes an early embryo during this time. After a few days, the embryo goes into the uterus and places itself in the uterine wall. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>IVF can be considered as a fallopian tube bypass. The stimulation is given to the ovaries with an injection. The injection has a fertility drug that helps create multiple eggs. Blood tests and transvaginal ultrasound helps reveal when the eggs become mature. By a minor procedure and giving a mild anaesthetic, the matured eggs are retrieved carefully through the vagina. The eggs are then delicately put in a petri dish and exposed to the sperm. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>The next day the eggs are examined thoroughly to see whether the fertilization took place successfully. If it did, they are left in the petri dish to divide and turn into embryos. After a few days later, one or more than one embryo is placed in the womanâ€™s uterus. It is a simple procedure that is usually not really uncomfortable than a standard Pap test. The extra embryos are studied in detail by the IVF laboratory personnel. If those embryos are viable, then they are frozen for the future use by a couple or the mother. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>In Vitro Fertilization is a technologically advanced method. It was first successful in England in the year 1978. It was initially used to treat infertility caused by the blocked fallopian tube. Today, it has evolved to be an effective method for all kinds of problems relating to infertility. The number of successful cases with IVF has come a long way since it was first established. Patients with favorable prognosis have a higher chance of successful IVF treatment than others. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>IVF Laboratory Procedure-</h3> \r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Assisted Hatching</li>\r\n	<li>Fertilization with intracytoplasmic sperm injection (ICSI)</li>\r\n	<li>Freezing embryo</li>\r\n	<li>Oocyte/ovarian tissue cryopreservation</li>\r\n	<li>Preimplantation genetic diagnosis (PGD)</li>\r\n	<li>Genetic Screening for Chromosome Anomalies</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Emotional Support-</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>When it comes to infertility, people become a lot more stressed than usual. It is overwhelming for them to know about the situation and sometimes cannot cope with the distress. Our physicians are trained to give all the care and support to such patients and the infertility nurses provide ongoing educational with emotional support too. They give guidance to couples who go through such trying times. Some of the methods that we use for stress reduction are Acupuncture and guided imagery. The nurses work closely with mental health nurses and psychiatrists to make the process better. The patients would benefit with such collaboration as they will be guided by experts from the field of psychology. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n','In Vitro Fertilization','','publish','closed','closed','','in-vitro-fertilization','','','2018-03-27 18:37:22','2018-03-27 13:07:22','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=65',0,'department','',0),(66,1,'2018-03-27 18:37:52','2018-03-27 13:07:52','<h2>Internal Medicine and Critical Care </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Department of internal medicine and critical care gives a complete primary care service in an outpatient service basis along with providing holistic care to the patients who are hospitalized and are suffering from a wide range of ailments. This department is fully equipped to manage chronic issues and other major health conditions such heart diseases or diabetes, acute respiratory infections and joint paints. We have a team of certified physicians for internal medicine, paediatrics, nurses, geriatrics, medical assistants and experienced support staff.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Internal medicine or general medicine is about the diagnosis, treatment, prevention of diseases that take place amongst adults. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Medical procedure available â€“ </h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Blood pressure test- To measure the pressure in the arties of the heart as it pumps. People with high blood pressure (hypertension), low blood pressure (hypotension) and prehypertension will need to do regular BP check. </li>\r\n\r\n	<li>C-reactive protein- When there is inflammation in the body, CRP levels gets disturbed. The doctor may check a patientâ€™s CRP level for treatment of infection or for other medical conditions. </li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Allergy skin test- Exposure to various forms of allergens is made to done so that the real cause of allergy is known with signs of allergic reactions.</li> \r\n\r\n	<li>Haemoglobin test- To measure the amount of haemoglobin in the blood, such a test is done. Haemoglobin is a kind of protein in the blood that carries oxygen to the bodyâ€™s organ and transfer the carbon dioxide from the tissues and organs back to the respiratory organs, the lungs. People are anaemic if they have low count of red blood cells. </li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Hematocrit test- These tests determines whether a person has too much or too few red blood cells. A sample of blood is taken for test </li>\r\n\r\n	<li>Cytochrome P450 tests (CYP450 tests)- Cytochrome P450  test helps to know about the metabolism of a drug that a person takes. How well a person processes a drug, is known through this test. Because our genetic traits are different from others, it causes variations in the enzymes. This is why it creates a difference in medication for all. This test is becoming quite common nowadays as it provides a clue to why some antidepressants work on some people and not on others. In short it helps in indicating the affects of medications on people. \r\n	 These tests are built to help a doctor understand the patientâ€™s problem faster. The subspecialty of inter medicine come under almost all disciplines. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n','Internal Medicine and Critical Care','','publish','closed','closed','','internal-medicine-and-critical-care','','','2018-03-27 18:37:52','2018-03-27 13:07:52','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=66',0,'department','',0),(67,1,'2018-03-27 18:38:32','2018-03-27 13:08:32','<h2>Laparoscopic and General Surgery </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Laparoscopy is a kind of surgery that is done on the pelvic or abdomen region through small incisions with the help of a camera. With a few tiny cuts and the help of a laparoscope, therapeutic intervention and diagnosis is done.  There are number of advantages by going for this process in comparison to the open procedure. Reduced pain due smaller incision, shorter recovery period, less chances of haemorrhage   are some of the benefits. This kind of surgery is also called a keyhole surgery because of the method it uses. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Instruments that are used for this surgery are- </h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Scissors</li>\r\n<li>Forceps</li>\r\n<li>Hooks</li>\r\n<li>Probes</li>\r\n<li> retractor </li>\r\n<li>others</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>There are mainly 2 types of laparoscope methods- </h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>a digital laparoscope where a tiny digital video camera is put at the end of the laparoscope, removing the rod lens system</li>\r\n<li>A telescope rod lens that is usually connected to a video camera. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>The first kind of mechanism mentioned above helps give a better visual picture with the flexible endoscope, substituting with the traditional fiberscope. </h3>\r\n\r\n<strong>General surgery and laparoscopic medical procedures- </strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Abdominal ultrasound scan test</li>\r\n<li>Vasectomy</li>\r\n<li>Tonsillectomy</li>\r\n<li> Myomectomy</li>\r\n<li> Cholecystectomy</li>\r\n<li>Thyroidectomy</li>\r\n<li>Rectal prolapse surgery</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Our hospital has all the latest technology and infrastructure to support patients. The experienced doctors take their time to consult with the patient and have an open discussion about the case. Depending on the severity of the case, actions are taken with the patientâ€™s consent. Patients get the latest treatments, specialized assessments along with counselling and clinical post-op care. All the medications and regular follow ups are planned by the doctors so that the recovery is smooth. The advantage of Laparoscopic surgery is its short hospital stays after the process. The scars are minimal. \r\n</p>','Laparoscopic and General Surgery','','publish','closed','closed','','laparoscopic-and-general-surgery','','','2018-03-27 18:38:32','2018-03-27 13:08:32','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=67',0,'department','',0),(68,1,'2018-03-27 18:39:12','2018-03-27 13:09:12','<h2>Medical, Surgical and neonatal ICU </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>An Intensive Care Unit of a hospital is the most restricted area. Only the doctors, nurses and staff with occasional family visits are allowed in order to prevent the patient from having any kind of infection. Superior level of hygiene is maintained in this section as the patient is in a major recovery mode from a long surgery and is quite weak. \r\nOur hospital has Surgical, Medical and Neonatal ICUs.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>MICU (Medical Intensive Care Unit)</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Medical Intensive Care Unit is just like an ICU but deals with narrower range of medical issues. Those with medical cases come up under this setting. For example a patient might require insulin through IV or dealing with drug overdose, etc. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>SICU (Surgical intensive care unit)</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Our hospital has provisions for surgical intensive care unit that has beds for patients who have undergone specialty and general surgical process. This includes trauma (trauma ICU), all gastrointestinal procedures, renal, liver and pancreas transplantation and also all other surgery related procedures except cardiothoracic. Our ICU room consists of surgical intensivist or anaesthesiologist, both junior and experienced anaesthesiology residents and a multidisciplinary team of related health care providers. Proper management, organized rotation of staff, accurate assessments, initial resuscitation, post-op recovery is donefrom a huge variety of operating disciplines that contains general, orthopaedic, vascular, head and neck, transplantations and urologic. The fellows of critical care spend time as much as 3 to 4 months directly managing all the work relating to triage decisions, patient care, coordination and transfers, in and out of the SICU. Gradually, the critical care fellows take over the responsibilities of supervising the care given by the multidisciplinary teams of junior and experienced senior residents from surgical and anaesthesiology specialties, including all the necessary procedures. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Neonatal ICU</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>A birth of a child is the most delicate time for the mother and the baby. Today, due to advanced medical systems and technology, it has become far easier to take care of babies when born. It is very important to look after the health of the child post birth as the body is still fragile to the new world it entered. Our hospital has special rooms and facilities for neonatal care. NICU is very highly developed and sophisticated instruments are used to make sure that the baby is fine.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>NICU is a specific unit that takes care of new-borns who are ill or premature infants. Neonatal essentially means the first 28 days of life after birth. Neonatologists take care of the NICU along with other nurses, physicians, pharmacists, dieticians and respiratory physicians. We have neonatal nurses who specifically look into the overall health of the babies with risks. They have special skills to take care of them since illness or prematurity is a high risk factor. Our nurses practice their skills in the delivery room, emergency rooms, ICUs and special clinic.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>The neonatal incubator-</strong> Observation, oxygenation, preservation from cold temperature, provision of nutrition via intravenous catheter, medications, maintenance of fluid balance takes place in our incubator. </li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Transportable incubator- </strong>An incubator that can be used to transport the baby from one hospital to another for better medical facilities is available here. It has mini ventilator, pulse oxymeter, IV pump, cardio-respiratory monitor and oxygen supply built on the frame. </li>\r\n\r\n<li>Other equipments to evaluate the babyâ€™s health include BP monitors, ventilator, and oxygen hoods. \r\nNICU diagnosis and pathologies- Jaundice, Apnea, anaemia, Bronchopulmonary dysplasia (BPD),Intraventricular haemorrhage,  neonatal sepsis, Bradycardia, infant respiratory distress syndrome and many other problems are treated here. </li>\r\n</ul>','Medical, Surgical and neonatal ICU','','publish','closed','closed','','medical-surgical-and-neonatal-icu','','','2018-03-27 18:39:12','2018-03-27 13:09:12','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=68',0,'department','',0),(69,1,'2018-03-27 18:39:40','2018-03-27 13:09:40','<h2>Microbiology </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Essentially, microbiology deals with the analysis of microorganisms. Our Microbiology department deals with its sub-disciplines- parasitology, bacteriology, virology, immunology and serology services under microbiology. Accurate results are found in very little time so that the investigation and treatment start as early as possible. With proper and updated equipment the microbiology services are done without any problems. Many tests are done here, from routine tests to molecular diagnostic analysis.</p> \r\n\r\n<h3>The tests that are carried in this department are as follows- </h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Stool DNA test- The identification of changes in a DNA cell of a stool sample is done through this test. It is non-invasive lab test. </li>\r\n	<li>Faecal occult blood test- This is a test done to find out whether there is hidden blood in the stool. </li>\r\n	<li>Urinalysis- For the identification of disorders like urinary tract infection, diabetes or kidney infection, urinalysis is done. Such examination/analysis is done by taking a sample of the urine. </li>\r\n	<li>Microalbumin tests- This test is done to identify levels of blood protein in the urine.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n','Microbiology','','publish','closed','closed','','microbiology','','','2018-03-27 18:39:40','2018-03-27 13:09:40','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=69',0,'department','',0),(70,1,'2018-03-27 18:40:09','2018-03-27 13:10:09','<h2>Neonatology </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As soon as an ill baby is born or a premature birth takes place, they are taken to the neonatology department for better and faster check-up. Special training under the pediatric studies are done for doctors and nurses to work in the neonatology. It is usually practiced under NICU. \r\n </p>\r\n \r\n<p>A child with birth defects, low weight, sepsis, birth asphyxia, pulmonary hypoplapsia or congenital malformation has to be admitted to NICU. The weak body of the newborn needs individual care and facilities hence our neonatal department has special incubators, monitoring systems and other check up tools designed for the infant. \r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The neonatal diseases that are of concerns in an infant are as follows- </h3>\r\n <ul>\r\n	<li>Jaundice</li>\r\n	<li>Bowel obstruction</li>\r\n	<li>Meningitis</li>\r\n	<li>Hepatitis</li>\r\n	<li>Seizures</li>\r\n	<li>Stoke </li>\r\n	<li>Acne</li>\r\n	<li>Conjunctivitis</li>\r\n	<li>Tetanus</li>\r\n	<li>Hypoglycaemia</li>\r\n	<li>Tetanus</li>\r\n	<li>Transmitted diseases</li>\r\n	<li>Infant distress respiratory syndrome</li>\r\n	<li>Lupus erythematosus</li>\r\n	<li>Cholstasis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Universal thyroid screen checking and Immunization is done on every newborn baby. Every kind of emergencies for ill newborn are given who need intensive care. All babies who have high risk to life are followed up for a month of age and then would be transferred to the pediatrics. It also shows the preventive aspect of childbirth care as an invaluable and undividable component of Neonatology. After the sick and preterm babies are discharged from the NICU, they get the best neurodevelopment support and follow up till the babies turn 6. The nutritional assessments, physiotherapy, developmental assessment, language, speech, ophthalmological analysis are carried out on these babies. Hence, neonatology becomes the integral part in the preliminary or initial assessments of the babies. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We take holistic care of the baby with state-of-art facilities. We also have the ECMO support for infants and babies that have life-threatening issues. We are also equipped with the transportation of sick neonates from other hospitals/centres. </p> \r\n\r\n<strong>Neonatal Screening Service- </strong>\r\n\r\nThis service is done on babies for detecting kind of hearing loss, congenital adrenal hyperplasia, hypothyroidism, critical congenital heart diseases and metabolic disorders for the newborn.\r\n \r\n<strong>Other services- </strong>\r\n <ul>\r\n	<li>For women we have services that include antenatal, inter - partum clinical services, Pre-conceptual clinical services.</li>\r\n	<li>Laboratory supports for pregnant women, new mother and postpartum women. </li>\r\n	<li>Medical/diagnostic imaging services for pregnant women, postpartum women and newborns. </li>\r\n	<li>Excellent perinatal and neonatal services by skilled and qualified professionals. </li>\r\n	<li>The neonatal department is open 24 hours every day. </li>\r\n	<li>The maternal and neonatal transport facilities are available as well. </li>\r\n	<li>Facilities like cardiac surgery and paediatric surgery is done in our hospital.</li>\r\n</ul>','Neonatology','','publish','closed','closed','','neonatology','','','2018-03-27 18:40:09','2018-03-27 13:10:09','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=70',0,'department','',0),(71,1,'2018-03-27 18:40:41','2018-03-27 13:10:41','<h2>Nephrology and Dialysis</h2> \r\n\r\n<p>The Nephorology department gives comprehensive care across a wide spectrum of kidney diseases. The department has facilities that are engineered to give excellent care and positive results.  Our hospital has a team of experienced and qualified doctors who are recognised for their well developed clinical skills. They have great knowledge to treat all categories of patients, be it elders or children.  We have an eminent group of people who specialize in kidney transplants, who are nephrologists, urologists with technical expertise that meet the challenges of the life needs. Our diagnostics are the most technically advanced with dialysis that is comprehensively evaluated. The latest tools are vailable for surgical procedures and a diligent post-operative care is done to minimize the chances of infection.  </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The dialysis-</h3> \r\n\r\n<p>Dialysis is a way to substitute the normal functions of the kidney. Patients who have had renal failure need to be on dialysis so that they can lead a normal life. There are mainly two kinds of dialysis- </p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Peritoneal dialysis- This method uses fluid that is put into the patientâ€™s abdominal cavity to eliminate the fluids and waste products from the body. </li>\r\n  <li>Hemodialysis â€“ This method involves the machine, removing the wastes and fluids from the blood of the patient.</li> \r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Dialysis is a service that is available in our hospital where the nephrologists keep a close eye on the work along with the nurses and official haemodialysis technicians. We also have dieticians who are registered with us. Nocturnal, peritoneal and short daily dialysis is offered to both adults and children. \r\nIt is a temporary solution to an acute injury to the kidney. If someone is looking for a permanent solution, they have to undergo a kidney transplant but it is only for those who can undergo it. That is the reason dialysis was invented. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Medical practices under nephrology:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Blood urea nitrogen level- This is a common kind of blood test. The blood urea nitrogen test shows important information about how the liver and kidneys are functioning. It is a test that measures the quantity of urea nitrogen thatâ€™s present in the blood. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>This is how the body typically eliminates the urea nitrogen from the nitrogen-</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>The liver generates ammonia, which carries nitrogen, after it cracks down the protein used by the cells of the body. </li>\r\n  <li>The nitrogen collaborates with other elements such s hydrogen, carbon and oxygen to create urea, which is a chemical waste product. </li>\r\n  <li>The urea goes all the way from the liver to the kidneys through a personâ€™s bloodstream.</li>\r\n  <li>The healthy kidneys filter urea and eliminate other kinds of waste products from the blood </li>\r\n  <li>This filtered waste is then prepared to leave the body through urination.</li>\r\n</ul> \r\n\r\n<p>The Blood urea nitrogen level test determines whether the nitrogen levels are normal or higher than usual. If itâ€™s higher than normal, this suggests that the liver or kidney may not be functioning properly. </p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	\r\n<li><strong>Hemodialysis-</strong> In hemodialysis, the machine filters out salt, wastes and fluids from the blood when the kidney function level is no longer working in its adequate form. It is one of the most common methods to cure advanced kidney failure. This method can help one lead an active life despite having failed kidneys. Once person goes for this treatment, they have to follow a strict schedule and medications on a regular basis. There will be changes in the diet that the patient has to adhere to. It is a serious responsibility so the patient must think before he/she takes the step, although we will always be there to support them. Our health care team will be there to encourage and take care of the patients. Kidney specialists and other experts will be there to manage the hemodialysis as well. There are facilities to do tis treatment at home too. </li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Intravenous pyelogram-</strong> This treatment is also called an excretory urogram. An X-ray is taken of the urinary tract and lets the doctor see the kidneys, bladder and the tube from where the urine travels from kidney to the bladder. An Intravenous pyelogram is used to diagnose problems that affect the urinary tract. Disorders like kidney stones, kidney cysts, enlarged prostate and urinary tract tumour are diagnosed here. In this test, a patient will have an X-ray dye injected into their system, i.e., through the veins of the arm. This will flow into the kidney, bladder, ureters and outline each of the structures. A specific number of times are required to take the X-ray so that the doctor can get a clear picture of the urinary tract and make a thorough assessment about how healthily itâ€™s working. </li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Kidney biopsy-</strong> This procedure is also called renal biopsy. The doctors remove a small part of the kidney tissue to examine it under the microscope for any signs of disease or damage. Often doctors recommend such biopsies to find out any suspicious matter with the kidneyâ€™s function. It is also done to find out the severity of the disease and monitor a proper treatment for the disease. The patient may need a biopsy if they have had a kidney transplant that is not functioning the way it should be. Many a times a doctor does a kidney biopsy by putting a needle through the skin. This procedure is known as percutaneous kidney biopsy. We keep an imaging device that helps the doctor to guide the needle into the kidney for removing the tissue.</li> \r\n\r\n<li><strong>Creatinine test-</strong> To determine any kind of problems in the kidney, creatinine test is recommended. Creatinine is a type of chemical waste which is produced by the muscle metabolism and by eating meat in a similar way.  A healthy kidney will filter the creatinine and other wastes from the blood. This filtered waste produce leaves the body via urine. If the kidneys are not functioning adequately, this may indicate an increased level of accumulated creatnine in the blood. A serum creatinine test can measure the level of creatinine in the blood and let one know the estimate of how well the kidneys are filtering them. It is called glomerular filtration rate. Similarly a creatnine urine test can calculate the creaitnine in a personâ€™s urine.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Nephrology and Dialysis','','publish','closed','closed','','nephrology-and-dialysis','','','2018-03-27 18:40:41','2018-03-27 13:10:41','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=71',0,'department','',0),(72,1,'2018-03-27 18:41:12','2018-03-27 13:11:12','<strong>Neurology Department </strong>\r\n\r\n<p>People suffering from problems of the nervous system go to a neurologist. A humanâ€™s nervous system is a very delicate, complex and it regulates and coordinates the body activities. The two major divisions in the nervous system are </p>\r\n <ul>\r\n	 <li>Central nervous system- brain and the spinal cord.</li>\r\n	 <li>Peripheral nervous system- it consists of neural elements and sensory receptors. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We treat several patients with numerous neurological conditions. It includes the conditions like movement disorders, speech and language disorder, epilepsy, cognitive disorders, neurodegenerative diseases like dementia, Alzheimer\'s disease, Parkinsonâ€™s disease or Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis. Others like headache disorders, spinal cord disorder, seizure disorders, infections of the brain stroke and cerebrovascular disorders are also treated here. There are several other disorders that a neurologist treat but they do not perform surgeries. If a patient has to, they refer them to a neurosurgeon. </p>\r\n \r\n<h3>A number of tests are done in our hospital-</h3> \r\n <ul>\r\n	 <li>Biopsies </li>\r\n	 <li>Lumbar punctures</li>\r\n	 <li>Carotid artery ultrasound</li>\r\n	 <li>Electroencephalogram (EEG)</li>\r\n	 <li>Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI) of the Spine and Brain</li>\r\n	 <li>Evoked Potentials Studies (EP)</li>\r\n	 <li>Electromyography (EMG)</li>\r\n	 <li>Computed Tomography (CT or CAT) Scan of the Brain</li>\r\n	 <li>Positron Emission Tomography (PET) Scan</li>\r\n	 <li>Nerve Conduction Velocity (NCV)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The treatments for the common neurological diseases are medicines. Our doctors have wide knowledge of updated medications that are available. They are also well-informed about the investigational drug therapies that are in talks.</p>\r\n \r\n<p>For surgeries, they work in collaboration with some of the skilled and educated neurosurgeons. They will make referrals based on the situation of the case and study for whatâ€™s the best for the patients. A proper discussion is done to come down to a suitable treatment for the patient.</p>\r\n\r\n<strong>The neurosurgeon are experienced in the field of</strong>\r\n <ul>\r\n	 <li>Spine</li>\r\n	 <li>Peripheral nerve</li>\r\n	 <li>Neuroendocrine</li>\r\n	 <li>Peripheral nerve</li>\r\n	 <li>Brain and spinal tumour</li>\r\n	 <li>Pain management</li>\r\n	 <li>Epilepsy</li>\r\n	 <li>Brain surgery and trauma</li>\r\n	 <li>Paediatric neurosurgery</li>\r\n	 <li>Functional neurosurgery</li>\r\n	 <li>Stroke</li>\r\n	 <li>Facial pain</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The Neurology department of our hospital has the potential to eliminate diseases with some of our great expertise and up-to-date technology. Some of the well-known doctors are there to help the patient with utmost care. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Neurology Department','','publish','closed','closed','','neurology-department','','','2018-03-27 18:41:12','2018-03-27 13:11:12','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=72',0,'department','',0),(73,1,'2018-03-27 18:41:43','2018-03-27 13:11:43','<h2>Neurosciences Brain and spine </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This department deals with the study of the nervous system of the body. It is a branch of biology that specifically studies molecular biology, anatomy, biochemistry, physiology of neurons and the neural circuits. Pharmacology, medicine and psychology are other fields that they work with, hand in hand. </p>\r\n\r\n<strong>The brain and the spine under the Neuroscience department work delicately. There are experts who look into the matter very carefully for the best results. We treat a number of diseases and conditions like-</strong>\r\n\r\n <ul>\r\n	 <li>Alzheimer\'s and Dementia</li>\r\n	 <li>Acoustic Neuroma</li>\r\n	 <li>ALS (Amyotrophic Lateral Sclerosis)</li>\r\n	 <li>Arteriovenous Malformation (AVM)</li>\r\n	 <li>Aphasia</li>\r\n	 <li>Bellâ€™s palsy</li>\r\n	 <li>Ataxia</li>\r\n	 <li>Back and neck pain</li>\r\n	 <li>Brain Aneurysm</li>\r\n	 <li>Central Nervous System Lymphoma</li>\r\n	 <li>Brain Tumor</li>\r\n	 <li>Concussions and Head Injuries</li>\r\n	 <li>Chiari Malformation</li>\r\n	 <li>Craniopharyngioma</li>\r\n	 <li>Head injuries and concussions</li>\r\n	 <li>Siezures and epilepsy</li>\r\n	 <li>Glioma</li>\r\n	 <li>Headache</li>\r\n	 <li>Craniopharyngioma</li>\r\n	 <li>Guillain-Barre Syndrome</li>\r\n	 <li>Migraine</li>\r\n	 <li>Landau-Kleffner Syndrome</li>\r\n	 <li>Meningitis</li>\r\n	 <li>Learning disorders</li>\r\n	 <li>Meningioma</li>\r\n	 <li>Muscular dystrophy</li>\r\n	 <li>Myasthenia Gravis</li>\r\n	 <li>Obsessive Compulsive Disorders (OCD)</li>\r\n	 <li>Neuromuscular disease</li>\r\n	 <li>Parkinsonâ€™s disease</li>\r\n	 <li>Osteogenesis Imperfecta</li>\r\n	 <li>Pituitary Tumour</li>\r\n	 <li>Schizophrenia</li>\r\n	 <li>Septicemia</li>\r\n	 <li>Spinal tumours</li>\r\n	 <li>Spinal cord injuries</li>\r\n	 <li>Traumatic Brain Injury</li>\r\n	 <li>Strokes</li>\r\n	 <li>Tension headaches</li>\r\n	 <li>Vascular malformation</li>\r\n	 <li>Torticollis</li>\r\n	 <li>Retinoblastoma</li>\r\n	 <li>Myasthenia Gravis</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Treatment and tests that we perform-</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>CT scan, Biofeedback therapy, Biopsy, Cerebral Angioplasty & Stenting, Deep brain stimulation, Craniotomy, Concussion baseline screening, Diffusion tensor imaging, electroencephalogram, endovascular coiling, gene therapy, Microsurgery, myelogram, neuropsychological tests, MR Spectroscopy, Electromyography, Vision therapy, Spinal tap, Sinus X-ray, Skull X-ray,  Radiation Therapy, Occupational therapy, Pipeline Embolization Device, Physical Therapy, Vagus Nerve Stimulation (VNS), Wingspan Stent.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>All of the services are provided for the patients to have a thorough investigation. The doctors work together and find appropriate solutions after a detailed discussion. All of the advantages and disadvantages are informed clearly. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hospitals have all the facilities to make sure that patients get the best treatment. All our diagnostic tools and other machines are well up to date. They meet the international standards and if any up gradation is needed, it is done without any further delay. The norms are followed diligently. Our hospital also has the facilities for emergency of any kind that is required. The neuroscience department is adept to all situations. The trained nurses and doctors have all the required management skills at the time of emergency. We maintain all the hygiene and cleanliness. The safety and quality is checked very frequently so that patients stay away from infections of any kind.</p> \r\n','Neurosciences Brain and spine','','publish','closed','closed','','neurosciences-brain-and-spine','','','2018-03-27 18:41:43','2018-03-27 13:11:43','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=73',0,'department','',0),(74,1,'2018-03-27 18:42:26','2018-03-27 13:12:26','<strong>OBS and Gynaecology</strong>\r\n\r\n<p>Our OBS and Gynaecology gives full range of womenâ€™s health care services. With superior quality techniques and best machines, we help give the patient a less painful experience in our hospital. We aim for painless deliveries, management of late pregnancies, looking into high risk pregnancy among some of the services. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We offer treatments through expert gynaecologists and specialists for particular disease groups. Women of any age group can come to our hospital with different health concerns. They are assessed and appropriately addressed to. Our team understands the value of life and knows how to treat many types of diseases like fibroids that includes open myomectomies that are unsuitable for endoscopic operations. </p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Some of our medical procedure under the OBS and Gynaecology department</h2>- \r\n <ul>\r\n <li>abdominal ultrasound scan test</li>\r\n <li>Breast MRI, Biopsy</li>\r\n <li>C-section</li>\r\n <li>Abdominal hysterectomy </li>\r\n <li>basal body temperature method </li>\r\n <li>Family planning</li>\r\n <li>Cervical cap</li>\r\n <li>Egg freezing</li>\r\n <li>Colposcopy</li>\r\n <li>endometrial ablation</li>\r\n <li>Chorionic villus sampling (CVS)</li>\r\n <li>Birth Control pills and awareness</li>\r\n <li>Contraceptive injections</li>\r\n <li>Dilation and curettage (D&C)</li>\r\n <li>Fetal ultrasound</li>\r\n <li>Condoms</li>\r\n <li>Fetal fibronectin  test</li>\r\n <li>HPV test</li>\r\n <li>IVF</li>\r\n <li>First trimester screening</li>\r\n <li>Intrauterine insemination</li>\r\n <li>Labor indiction</li>\r\n <li>Noninvasive prenatal testing (NIPT)</li>\r\n <li>Mirena is a hormonal intrauterine device (IUD)</li>\r\n <li>progestin-only birth control pill</li>\r\n <li>Nonstress test</li>\r\n <li>Oophorectomy (ovary removal surgeries)</li>\r\n <li>ParaGard (copper IUD)</li>\r\n <li>Pelvic exam</li>\r\n <li>Rhesus (Rh) factor blood test</li>\r\n <li>Sperm donation</li>\r\n <li>Spermicide</li>\r\n <li>Quad screen</li>\r\n <li>Vaginal hysterectomy </li>\r\n <li>Uterine artery embolization</li>\r\n <li>VBAC</li>\r\n <li>tubal ligation reversal</li>\r\n <li>Vasectomy reversal</li>\r\n <li>Vaccum extraction</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Every distress is discussed properly with the patient in an open manner. All the advantages and disadvantages are shown to them so that they are aware of the procedure that they choose. Once the decision is made, we make sure everything is done smoothly. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','OBS and Gynaecology','','publish','closed','closed','','obs-and-gynaecology','','','2018-03-27 18:42:26','2018-03-27 13:12:26','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=74',0,'department','',0),(75,1,'2018-03-27 18:43:17','2018-03-27 13:13:17','<h2>Orthopaedic and joint replacement</h2> \r\n\r\n<p>Due to age, accident/injury or deficiency in the bones, many suffer from joint pains and orthopaedic related problems. Our orthopaedic and joint replacement department have specialists in spinal injuries, arthroscopy, dealing with trauma patients and complex joint replacements are done here to make sure that the patient derives maximum health care for their joins and bones. </p> \r\n\r\n<p>We have doctors that are highly qualified and efficient line up of doctors from the country. We are dedicated to deliver the most suitable treatment in all issues especially major and minor osteoarthritic issues. With technology getting advanced every single moment, we ensure that our patients get the best ones. One of our treatments includes platelet-rich plasma transfusion. This is designed for patient suffering from osteoarthritis. The treatments in our hospital involve very minimally invasive surgeries for bone reconstruction and even trauma recovery. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>We have a great team of rheumatologists, rehabilitation experts and anaesthesiologists. They will help patients recover in a fast and quick manner. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>We provide the following medical procedures- </h3>\r\n <ul>\r\n <li>Ankle-brachial index</li>\r\n <li>Bone density test </li>\r\n <li>Bone scan</li>\r\n <li>Hip replacement</li>\r\n <li>Knee braces for osteoporosis</li>\r\n <li>Cortisone shots</li>\r\n <li>Lumbar puncture</li>\r\n <li>Spinal fusion</li>\r\n <li>Rheumatoid factor test</li>\r\n <li>Radiofrequency neurotomy </li>\r\n <li>Knee osteotomy</li>\r\n <li>Diskectomy</li>\r\n <li>Knee replacement surgery</li>\r\n <li>ACL reconstruction</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Problems in the joints can make a personâ€™s life very hard. They are not able to function like a normal person. Hence we also provide psychological support to our patients so that they are fit mentally to face all kind of diagnosis and treatments. Our team makes sure the patients do not have any kind of trouble at any step. Proper discussion, pro and cons are exchanges before any decision is taken. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Orthopaedic and joint replacement','','publish','closed','closed','','orthopaedic-and-joint-replacement','','','2018-03-27 18:43:17','2018-03-27 13:13:17','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=75',0,'department','',0),(76,1,'2018-03-27 18:44:13','2018-03-27 13:14:13','<h2>Paediatric Department </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As a saying goes, â€œone size does not fit allâ€. This department looks into the medicine and medical care for all the infants, children and adolescents. The medical doctors who specialize in this field are called paediatricians. Specialized treatments are given to children who suffer from various disorders and diseases. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>A wide variety of specialties come under the department, some of them are-</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Paediatric cardiology</li>\r\n<li>Paediatric nephrology</li>\r\n<li>Paediatric neurology</li>\r\n<li>Paediatric surgery</li>\r\n<li>Paediatric Orthopaedics</li>\r\n<li>Paediatric neonatal medicines</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We provide radiology, dentistry services for all age groups from newborns to adolescence. The healthcare needs for the children are a little different than adults. This is the reason why a separate section is made for them. Many a times separate priority is given to children with special needs that require different technology to heal them. Sick children who need critical care are taken care of by extremely dedicated professionals. We have NNICU, HDU, PICU in our hospital for every needs.</p> \r\n\r\n<p><strong>Facilities- </strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Miniature versions of all the facilities are available in our hospital. Our doctors make sure that they are caring, understanding and equally fun for children and make the process less stressful. There is always scope to do more and make it easier for them. We have Multi- Paediatric Super Specialities under One Roof. There are options for super deluxe, deluxe, standard and semi standard beds. For all children, we provide gaming zones and entertainment area where they can engage themselves in cartoons and other programmes. We have libraries that consist of books appropriate for children. There is a quiet atmosphere so that they can read in peace. A child development centre is available were they can get proper check up with personal care. The most advanced support systems are given to the child for the best treatment. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n','Paediatric Department','','publish','closed','closed','','paediatric-department','','','2018-03-27 18:44:13','2018-03-27 13:14:13','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=76',0,'department','',0),(77,1,'2018-03-27 18:45:01','2018-03-27 13:15:01','<h2>Pathology and Microbiology </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The microbiology section is entirely equipped with automated systems that involve tuberculosis culture, blood culture, resistance power, sensitivity and bacterial identification. Services for the study of rare microbes are also done in under this department.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Pathology section of our hospital has the most up-to-date technology for fastest diagnosis.  All kinds of diagnosis is done through this department with qualitative care.  The patient is the only priority in our hospital and this department focuses on that. The efficient staff helps maintain standards of the hospital. They respect a patientâ€™s privacy. </p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Some other scope of services â€“</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Immunology- </strong>It is a study of the immune system of all living organisms. All the diseases and disorders related to the failure of the immune system are determined under this section. It also deals with diseases of other systems which are closely connected to the immune system.  Immunodeficiency and autoimmunity are the two broad categories where diseases fall under. Disorders include hypersensitivity, asthma, allergies. The most widely known disease that affects the immune system is AIDS. Our department maintains standard procedures to test diseases and come to conclusions only after thorough results. </li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Clinical pathology-</strong> The analysis of blood fluids such as urine, blood, tissue homogenates come under clinical pathology. This sub-department work hand in hand using the tools of chemistry, molecular pathology, microbiology and hematology. </li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Histopathology- </strong>Our knowledgeable pathologists use well-equipped computerized tissue processor, embedding station and cryostat. The services consist of histopathological reporting, frozen sections histopathological reporting and immunohistochemistry. </li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Haematology- </strong>This section has an expert set of team for identification and cure of blood diseases. The haematologists examine and take care of the patients with many types of conditions like reduced or increased white blood cells, anemia, decrease or increase in platelets; hemorrhage or clotting disorders, swollen lymph nodes or spleen. This section of well-informed doctors also intends to cure blood cancer including problems like lymphoma, leukemia, multiple myeloma and other kinds of diseases and disorders as well. </li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Serology-</strong> A serology laboratory is for analysing the blood for any diseases that can affect the publicâ€™s health significantly. The measurement and detection of antibodies are done in this lab through a serology blood test. If people are exposed to antigens, i.e, viruses or bacteria, their immune system creates particular antibodies against the foreign organism. These antibody levelsare checked to determine if the infection took place recently or a long time ago. Our clinic conducts tests for blood-borne pathogens. This includes Hepatitis B, HIV and diseases that are risk to the general public. Tissue specimens of animal suspects are also taken for an investigation if an outbreak occurs. </li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Biochemistry-</strong> The biochemistry laboratory has various test menus serving various clinical specialties. The tests have top quality standards that for an all-around patient care. We have electrolyte analyzer, clinical chemistry auto-analyzer, semi-automated analyzer, immunoassay analyzer which is based on Electro Chemiluminescence and many more. All the equipments are connected to the management of the hospital so that quick results take place and all information is well updated. We also have the research work done in the laboratory on biomarkers in different diseases. </li>\r\n\r\n	<li><strong>Cytopathology- </strong>The diagnosis and study of diseases on a cellular level comes under the branch of pathology. Here, the study of free tissue fragments or cells are studied intricately. The identification of cancer and diagnosis of infectious diseases and inflammatory conditions are done here. Pap smear, a screening device to discover pre-cancerous cervical lesions, is used to know about cervical cancer. We have two methods to do the smear tests- Exfoliative cytology and Intervention cytology.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The equipment that we use are a huge range of auto-analysers. Some of our instruments are CELL-DYN 3700 Haematology analyser, Immuno-diagnostic analyser, Nephelometry analyser, Urine analyser, Biochemistry analyser. </p>\r\n\r\n<h4>Quality assurance of al the instruments are done on a frequent basis.</h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Our hospital staff is quite dedicated towards their work. They work diligently in all the services without any difference in the quality. Our pathology laboratory services have provided some of the finest facilities to the medical community. Because of this, we have earned a distinguished reputation of superiority, leadership and integrity. The commitment towards the service that we deliver will never go down and will continue to give exceptional results. \r\n</p>','Pathology and Microbiology','','publish','closed','closed','','pathology-and-microbiology','','','2018-03-27 18:45:01','2018-03-27 13:15:01','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=77',0,'department','',0),(78,1,'2018-03-27 18:45:40','2018-03-27 13:15:40','<h2>Physiotherapy</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>In our daily lives, one can find minor difficulties regarding the health. Many times, a person suffers with problems like back pain, muscle pull or other injuries in the body. Physical therapy is used to improve the quality of oneâ€™s life in terms of daily life. Diagnoses, prognosis of problems are done through physical examination and history. In many cases X-rays, MRIs and CT scans are required. The techniques used are some of the mechanical actions and forces (Bio-mechanics or Kinesiology), electro therapy, exercise therapy. Physiotherapy basically remediates impairments and helps a patient to move and function in a better way. Qualified physiotherapists are available in our hospital for the finest treatment. An open discussion is promoted so that all the problems are discussed without any hesitation. </p>\r\n \r\n<h2>A physiotherapist can support with the following process- </h2>\r\n <ul>\r\n	 <li>They help a patient with undertaking a comprehensive examination and assessment in order to better understand the requirement of the client or client group. </li>\r\n	 <li>Evaluation of the findings and come to a clinical judgement of the patient. </li>\r\n	 <li>Formulate a diagnosis, prognosis and a definitive plan for the patient.</li>\r\n	 <li>Provide an expert opinion for the patient and understand if the patient requires further consultation with another healthcare professional. </li>\r\n	 <li>Implementation of a physical therapist treatment/intervention programme.</li>\r\n	 <li>Find out the results of the treatment or intervention given</li>\r\n	 <li>Make a few other recommendations for health management in the future.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>Physiotherapy is available for â€“</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	  <li><strong>Muscle pain-</strong> cramps, pull, torn muscle, pulled hamstring, tight muscle, groin strain, spasm, abdominal spasm, fibromyalgia. </li>\r\n	 <li><strong>Joint pain- </strong>lupus, arthritis, degenerative joints, joint instability, poor alignment.</li>\r\n	 <li><strong>Postural Problems-</strong> muscle weakness, poor posture, muscle imbalance, round shoulders, scalpular instability, hypotonia.</li>\r\n	 <li><strong>Swelling and edema-</strong> lymphatic congestions, swollen joints, edema, lymphedema, chronic muscle inflammation or joint inflammation. </li>\r\n	 <li><strong>Foot pain-</strong> fallen arches, plantar fascilitis.</li>\r\n	 <li><strong>Bruising-</strong> contusions, bruising due to injuries or surgery.</li>\r\n	 <li><strong>Soft tissue injuries- </strong>tennis elbow, tendinitis, neck strain, back strain, rotator cuff injury, patellar tendinitis, whiplash, iliotibial band syndrome.</li>\r\n	 <li><strong>Joint injuries-</strong> joint sprain, dislocated joints, torn cartilage, joint hypermobility, unstable joints, sprained elbow/wrist//knee/ankle.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Physiotherapy helps improve the quality of life in many ways. It helps in keeping a healthy psychological mind as well as emotional and social well-being. We aim to have treatments that are discussed with the patient and their families. </p>\r\n \r\n<p>A professional physiotherapist will try to avoid giving medicines unless required on an urgent basis. </p>','Physiotherapy','','publish','closed','closed','','physiotherapy','','','2018-03-27 18:45:40','2018-03-27 13:15:40','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=78',0,'department','',0),(79,1,'2018-03-27 18:46:13','2018-03-27 13:16:13','<h2>Plastic and Cosmetic Surgery </h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This department has a very highly skilled and experienced team of surgeons and technicians. They use the best technology and use the most effective yet less invasive cosmetic reconstruction ways. Some of their successful and well known procedures are rhinoplasty, facelift, eyelid surgery, liposuction, breast augmentation and reduction, tummy tuck, breast lift, hair transplant, body lift, laser hair removal, laser resurfacing, hand surgery and other reconstructive surgeries.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><strong>Allergy skin tests- </strong>During this particular skin test, the persons are exposed to some specific things that they are allergic to. These allergy causing substance are observed for signs and symptoms of any reaction that they cause. A personâ€™s personal medical history is taken along with the allergen analysis so that both are correlated whether the substance one eats, touches, feels or smells is causing a problem or not. Allergy tests are done for asthma, food allergies, hay fever, latex allergy, dermatitis etc. </li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Arm lift-</strong> To improve the lower portion of the arm, people go for arm lift. The excess fat and skin is removed from between the elbow and the armpit. A more toned look is given to that part with newly repositioned contours by draping back skin over it. Toned arm creates a positive body image. Some do it because that part of the body sags faster. This procedure is also called brachioplasty.</li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Breast lift-</strong> A breast lift is commonly done to create a positive change to the breasts. Also called mastopexy, the surplus skin is eliminated and the breast tissue is redesigned to bring back the firmness of the breast. A sagging breast or the nipples pointing downwards at an early age can be a cue to lift the breasts. This improves self confidence and self image. This process does not change the size of the breast but only reshapes it. However, sizes can be changed if requested earlier. Hence both a lift and augmentation or reduction can be done together. </li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Botox injection- </strong>To temporarily paralyze the muscle activity, botox injections is used. A set of medication that uses many forms of botulinum toxin is used to do such an activity. Botox injection is essentially used to remove wrinkles form the face. They are also used to treat repetitive neck spasms, overactive bladder and excessive sweating. For some people it also works to treat migraines. Uses of botox include removing frown lines, horizontal lines, forehead furrows. </li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Jawline reconstruction- </strong>To shape the jawline, this surgery is done. Contouring and giving it a sharp chisel look is the most common demand of the patients. </li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Liposuction- </strong>To remove the excessive fat from certain parts of a personâ€™s body is done. It is a surgical procedure that is done with suction technique from areas like hips, thighs, abdomen, arms, neck or buttocks. Liposuction has the capability to shape the areas as well. Different countries have different name for this procedure such as body contouring or lipoplasty. Liposuction is commonly mistaken for weight loss method or an alternative to weight loss. If a person is obese or overweight then they have chances of weight loss through exercise, diet or via bariatric process like the gastric bypass surgery. They are less likely to lose it through liposuction. A candidate is eligible for liposuction if she/she has excessive body fat in particular areas of the body but otherwise have a normal body weight. </li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Dermabrasion-</strong> This procedure is a skin resurfacing method that is done through a rotating machine to sand the external layer of the skin. This procedure helps make the skin smoother and younger. It can eliminate the appearance of the visibly fine facial lines and help improve the look of scars. Scars like acne can be treated through such a process. It can be done alone or can be combined with other cosmetic procedures. Dermabrasion is a fairly new procedure. Depending on the extent of the treatment, a general anaesthesia can be used so that no pain is felt. The area of the skin where dermabrasion is done can become sensitive and pink for a few weeks. The pinkness may take duration of at least 3 months to fade away.</li>\r\n\r\n<li>F<strong>ace transplant-</strong> Facelift or rhytidectomy is a kind of cosmetic surgery that deals with improving oneâ€™s face and neck. During this procedure, the facial soft tissues are raised.  A neck lift or platysmaplasty is usually done together with the face lift. </li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Septoplasty-</strong> it is a surgery that helps correct a personâ€™s deviated nasal septum. By that we mean a displacement of the cartilage and bone that separates the two nostrils. During this procedure, the nasal septum is straightened and relocated in the middle of the nose. A surgeon may have to cut and remove the parts of a patientâ€™s septum before reinserting it in the proper place. If a patient wants to undergo a septoplasty, they need to consider a surgeonâ€™s advise and should have symptoms like breathing difficulties. The features and physical structure of the nose has to be taken into account. An open communication with the patient about the benefits and disadvantages of septoplasty is done in order to maintain clarity.</li> \r\n\r\n<li><strong>Tummy tuck-</strong> For those who want their abdomen to look slimmer/linear, they can go for tummy tuck. This procedure is also called abdominoplasty. It is a cosmetic surgery where the excess fat and tissue from that area is subtracted. In some cases the connective tissues are in the abdomen are made tighter with sutures too. This kind of surgery boosts oneâ€™s body image immensely. </li>\r\n\r\nâ€¢<li><strong>Brow lift-</strong> A forehead lift, is a cosmetic surgery that helps in improving a personâ€™s physical appearance. A soft tissue of the forehead including the skin of it is raised in certain way. </li>\r\n\r\n<li><strong>Blepharoplasty-</strong> this kind of surgery is done to fix droopy eyelids by a possibility of removing the excess skin, fat and muscles. The droopy eyes occur as one ages and the multiple folds take place over or under the eyelid. This causes sagging, eyebrows or bags under the eye. It affects the vision in many ways and causes discomfort to the patient. His surgery is done on an outpatient basis. All the risks and benefits are discussed properly before going for the procedure. </li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>All of the above procedures are done with a lot of detailed discussion and great care. Our staff looks into every case very deeply and advices if the procedures they want is necessary or not. Our technology match with international standards and our experts ensure everything goes accurately and smoothly.</p> \r\n\r\n','Plastic and Cosmetic Surgery','','publish','closed','closed','','plastic-and-cosmetic-surgery','','','2018-03-27 18:46:13','2018-03-27 13:16:13','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=79',0,'department','',0),(80,1,'2018-03-27 18:53:20','2018-03-27 13:23:20','<h2>PYSCHIATRY</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Mental health is one of the highest causes for concern among the growing population. Today, every person has so much of stress in their life that it is becoming increasingly difficult to cope with. The cause of unhealthy mental state of mind may be because of many reasons like physical health or environmental or external pressures. There is a huge connection between the mind and the body. If the body is weak, the mind gets affected easily and the opposite is also true. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our mission is to eliminate the stress through various therapy and medicines so that patients can cope with their daily life in a better way. There will be humane treatment with the creation of compassionate and efficient manpower. We also look into research that has taken the aspect of social responsibilities to develop a healthy nation. The psychiatry department has the great facilities to treat mental illness of any kind. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>All our professionals have had proper training and have been recruited on strict basis so that the quality of treatment is not hampered. The modern facilities are also included in the psychiatric social work department and clinical psychology as well.</p> \r\n\r\n<p><strong>Some of the features -</strong> </p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Medical management of Psychiatric disorders</li>\r\n<li>Psychotherapy </li>\r\n<li>Disagnostics</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>A wide range of neuropsychological evaluation is done along with psychotherapy, that includes- </h3>\r\n	\r\n<p><strong>Facilities:</strong></p>\r\n<ul>	\r\n<li>Intelligence tests</li>\r\n<li>Memory tests</li>\r\n<li>Personality tests</li>\r\n<li>Projective tests</li>\r\n<li>Aptitude test</li>\r\n<li>Cognitive behavioural therapy (CBT)</li>\r\n<li>Behaviour modification test</li>\r\n<li>Play therapy</li>\r\n<li>Couples therapy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>We can also offer different formats of therapies such as via online or telephone, if the patient canâ€™t come or wishes to. There are also under the talks of virtual reality therapy, which is computer-assisted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Therapies are customized according to the patientâ€™s needs. Some patients may need 12 sessions, some weeks and some more than that. Therapy depends on the doctorâ€™s analysis of the problem. The goal to eliminate the root of the problem is of utmost importance. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>With advanced development, we aim to make a healthier mind as much as possible. </p>\r\n\r\n\r\n','PYSCHIATRY','','publish','closed','closed','','pyschiatry','','','2018-03-27 18:53:20','2018-03-27 13:23:20','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=80',0,'department','',0),(81,1,'2018-03-27 18:54:04','2018-03-27 13:24:04','<h2>Radiology USG X-ray CT Scan</h2>\r\nThe department of radiology has all the services available related to it. A full range of services related to USG, X-RAY and CT scan is present in our hospital. The technologically advanced medical state-of-art machines make us the best to provide a proper diagnostic output. This department has extremely skilled radiologists and technicians who help you in every step. The dedication to offer services 24x7 is their top most goals. We aspire to push the boundaries in the radiology section and imaging through different kind of research activities.\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>USG- USG is an imaging technique for various conditions. An abdominal ultrasound is done to look for any diseases that may have affected the liver, kidney, pancreas and gallbladder. Generally, ultrasound is done for determining the problems in the muscles, tendons, blood vessels, joints and internal organs as mentioned previously. The aim is to find the source of the disease or to eliminate any pathology. It is used on pregnant women by using the ultrasound. This is practiced widely around the world.</li>\r\n 	<li>X-Ray- This is form electromagnetic radiation. Itâ€™s usually used to detect broken bones. But there are several other reasons to use it as well like chest x-rays are done to detect pneumonia or mammograms are done to determine breast cancer.</li>\r\n 	<li>CT Scan (Computerized Tomography)- A series of x-rays are taken from different angles and in great details. The computer processes cross sectional images of the soft tissues and bones inside the body. The result of the images can be analyzed like a one cuts a single slice of bread from its loaf. The analysis of each image is done in great detail. If required, additional visualization to view the body from another angle is also done. In some situations, CT scan is combined with 3D imaging systems. It provides more insight about the body than a normal plain x-ray. There are several uses of a CT scan in hospitals/clinics. Many use it particularly to find out about any sort of internal injury from an accident or other traumas, as soon as possible. It is used to picture almost all parts of a human body.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAll our facilities are up to date and sufficient for patients. A prior appointment is all they need to take for the exam. Our staff is very qualified to assess and conduct these exams seamlessly.','Radiology USG X-Ray CT Scan','','publish','closed','closed','','radiology-usg-x-ray-ct-scan','','','2019-02-10 16:54:14','2019-02-10 11:24:14','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=81',0,'department','',0),(82,1,'2018-03-27 18:54:46','2018-03-27 13:24:46','<h2>Skin and Laser treatment</h2>\r\nLaser and skin treatments are required for many reasons. Our diagnosis, treatment and facilities for such procedures remain unmatchable.\r\n<h3>Treatment options at our clinic-</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Kidney stone removal</li>\r\n 	<li>Celulite and striae</li>\r\n 	<li>Acne</li>\r\n 	<li>Psoriasis</li>\r\n 	<li>Vitiligo</li>\r\n 	<li>Botox</li>\r\n 	<li>Laser surgery</li>\r\n 	<li>Microdermabrasion</li>\r\n 	<li>Unwanted hair</li>\r\n 	<li>Chemical peels</li>\r\n 	<li>Radiofrequency</li>\r\n 	<li>Restylane</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nAll the procedures are done with careful and detailed discussion. An open communication between the doctor and the patients is extremely important and we abide by that rule. We also provide laser therapy alongside the treatments undergone by the patient like chemotherapy and other surgeries.Laser-induced interstitial thermotherapy is a way to treat cancers. This is done by using hyperthermia which radiates heat to shrink the tumour by killing or damaging the cancer. A laser is more accurate and creates lesser damage than surgeries that causes pain, swelling, bleeding and also scarring. It may be a bit more expensive than surgeries.\r\n\r\nLaser treatments are of various types. It depends on the patientâ€™s requirement. Some need laser treatment for removing dark spots, whitening, blemishes, hyperpigmentation, and permanent hair removal.\r\n\r\nAll our treatments are done by qualified doctors so that patient does not have to worry much.','Skin and Laser treatment','','publish','closed','closed','','skin-and-laser-treatment','','','2019-02-10 16:58:24','2019-02-10 11:28:24','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=82',0,'department','',0),(83,1,'2018-03-27 18:55:29','2018-03-27 13:25:29','<h2>Sports Injuries Management</h2>\r\nBeing fit and active is an advantage to a personâ€™s health, but sometimes there are risks of injuries. A special unit for sports injury management is setup in our hospital with some of the most qualified physicians. People from different sports background come to us for specific solutions.\r\n\r\nSports injury is often about soft tissue damages. From physiotherapist to major surgeries, everything is available here. Injuries on the ligament, muscle, joints or tendons are looked upon with utmost care.\r\n<h3>Two of the most widely known soft tissue damages are</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Tennis elbow- Also known as the golferâ€™s injury happens usually due to the overuse or over-extension of the elbow joints while playing any kind of racquet sports. However, tennis elbow is not limited to just sports injury because of the name. Any person can suffer from it depending on how they used their elbow joints.</li>\r\n 	<li>Sprained ankle- A sprained ankle happens due to the sudden turning or twisting movement of the ankle ligaments and muscles that leads to an excessive range of motion.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Our affective sports injury management consists of-</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Prevention</li>\r\n 	<li>Identification and treatment</li>\r\n 	<li>Rehabilitation</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Our physicians give appropriate adviceon how to prevent such injuries from happening or reoccurring again. Some of the tips that is common for all sports players are-</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Warming up thoroughly before and after playing sports</li>\r\n 	<li>Wearing the right footwear for proper grip</li>\r\n 	<li>Stay hydrated at all times.</li>\r\n 	<li>Strapping the vulnerable or previously injured portion as a preventive step.</li>\r\n 	<li>Over exertion, beyond a certain fitness level is highly prohibited.</li>\r\n 	<li>Correct techniques to be used for the training.</li>\r\n 	<li>Maintaining good level of fitness and muscle strength level.</li>\r\n 	<li>Gradual increase in the intensity of the training.</li>\r\n 	<li>Take advice from a qualified professional trainer only for any query.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nPlease see that the above mentioned recommendations or tips are not equivalent to a medical advice. Person suffering from any mild injury must consult our physician for further examination and assessment. In acute cases like reddening, swelling, tingling sensation, severe pain, and/or any neurological symptoms should be consulted by professionals.','Sports Injuries Management','','publish','closed','closed','','sports-injuries-management','','','2019-02-10 17:33:32','2019-02-10 12:03:32','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=83',0,'department','',0),(84,1,'2018-03-27 18:56:09','2018-03-27 13:26:09','<h2>Urology and Urosurgery</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>This department focuses on the medical diseases or surgical approaches towards the male and female urinary tract and only male reproductive system. Organs that include under the urology domain are the kidneys, ureters, adrenal glands, urethra, urinary bladder. The male reproductive systems include penis, seminal vesicles, testes, epididymis, and prostate.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The reproductive system and the urinary tract are very closely linked. The disorder of one often gets affected on the other. This is why a major spectrum of the conditions administered in urology exists under the field of genitourinary disorders. This department takes care of health conditions such as benign prostatic hyperplasia and urinary-tract infections. The surgical conditions are managed as well for prostate cancer, ladder cancer, kidney stones, traumatic injury, congenital abnormalities and stress incontinence.</p> \r\n\r\n<p>Our hospital has urological techniques include invasive laparoscopic surgery and robotic surgery, laser assisted surgeries and many more. Our urologists receive excellent training and know all the minimally invasive techniques of surgeries. They know about the fibre-optic endoscopic equipment, real time ultrasound guidance and many other laser treatments of multiple malignant and benign conditions.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>The sub-disciplines of urology are- </h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Nephrology- </li>\r\n	<li>Gynaecology</li>\r\n	<li>Urologic Oncology</li>\r\n	<li>Pediatric urology</li>\r\n	<li>Reconstructive urology</li>\r\n	<li>Andrology</li>\r\n	<li>Gastroenterology</li>\r\n	<li>Endocrinology</li>\r\n	<li>Colorectal surgery</li>\r\n	<li>Cytoscopy</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>The urology section of medicine is the most highly competitive and sought after surgical specialties for most of the physicians. With new technologies coming up, it is getting easier every day. The urologists have all the skills required for the procedures like erectile dysfunction, circumcision, abdominal ultrasound scan test, creatinine test etc. We maintain international standards and up to date knowledge on every changes that occur. </p>\r\n ','Urology and Urosurgery','','publish','closed','closed','','urology-and-urosurgery','','','2018-03-27 18:56:09','2018-03-27 13:26:09','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=84',0,'department','',0),(85,1,'2018-03-27 18:56:39','2018-03-27 13:26:39','<h2>Vascular Surgery</h2>\r\nVascular surgery is an operating subspecialty in which the diseases of the arteries, lymphatic circulation, veins (vascular system). It is managed by medical therapy by slightly invasive catheter technique and surgical reconstruction. The specialty has changed from general to cardiac surgery. It has also been pioneered by interventional radiology of a different kind. The surgeon is well trained in the management and diagnosis of the disease. This affects all parts of the vascular system except those of the brain and heart. The interventional cardiologists and cardiothoracic surgeons take care of the diseases of heart vessels whereas interventional neuroradiologists and neurosurgeons operatively take care of the diseases of the vessels located in the brain, for example intracranial aneurysms.\r\n\r\nSuch kind of surgery involves the surgery of carotid arteries, aorta, lower extremities that includes the femoral, iliac and tibial arteries. Vascular surgery also involves the operation of the vein for varicose veins and conditions like May-Thurner syndrome. In some places such a surgery also consists of transplant and dialysis access surgery.\r\n<h3>Some of the major diseases and categories of procedures that our hospital deals with are as follows-</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Abdominal aortic aneurysm (AAA) â€“ Open aortic surgery/ Endovascular Aneurysm Repair (EVAR)</li>\r\n 	<li>Carotid stenosis- Carotid stenting/Carotid endarterectomy</li>\r\n 	<li>Chronic kidney disease- Dialysis Ratheter Replacement/CiminoFistula</li>\r\n 	<li>Pulmonary embolism- Inferior vena cava filter/ Suction Thrombectomy</li>\r\n 	<li>Varicose veins- Vein stripping / Sclerotherapy/ Ambulatory phlebectomy/ Endovenous Laser Treatment.</li>\r\n 	<li>Pseudoaneurysm- Surgical ligation/ Covered stent.</li>\r\n 	<li>Thoracic aortic aneurysm- Thoracic Endovascular Aneurysmrepair/ Hybrid arch debranching</li>\r\n</ul>','Vascular Surgery','','publish','closed','closed','','vascular-surgery','','','2019-02-10 16:57:36','2019-02-10 11:27:36','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=85',0,'department','',0),(86,1,'2018-03-27 19:01:22','2018-03-27 13:31:22','<h2>pulmonary department</h2>\r\nThe pulmonary department offers services of Bronchoscopy that is both flexible and rigid. Diseases related to respiratory disorder and sleep disorders are looked upon in this department.\r\nAsthma, Pneumonia, COPD, Lung cancer, interstitial lung disease, TB, Breathing disorders are treated here. Pulmonary function test is done for comprehensive management and diagnosis of respiratory diseases. Bronchoscopes are also performed with the help of C-arm facility.\r\n<h3>Our services â€“</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Noninvasive Ventilation</li>\r\n 	<li>Complete Pulmonary Function Testing</li>\r\n 	<li>Pulmonary rehabilitation</li>\r\n 	<li>Biopsy of Pleura and Intra Thoracic Masses</li>\r\n 	<li>Smoking related diseases</li>\r\n 	<li>Asthma testing</li>\r\n 	<li>Diagnostic and Therapeutic Bronchoscope</li>\r\n</ul>','Pulmonary Department','','publish','closed','closed','','pulmonary-department','','','2019-02-10 17:02:29','2019-02-10 11:32:29','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=department&#038;p=86',0,'department','',0),(88,1,'2018-03-29 08:10:30','2018-03-29 02:40:30',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','88','','','2018-03-29 08:10:30','2018-03-29 02:40:30','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=88',1,'nav_menu_item','',0),(89,1,'2018-03-29 08:10:30','2018-03-29 02:40:30',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','89','','','2018-03-29 08:10:30','2018-03-29 02:40:30','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=89',2,'nav_menu_item','',0),(90,1,'2018-03-29 08:10:30','2018-03-29 02:40:30',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','90','','','2018-03-29 08:10:30','2018-03-29 02:40:30','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=90',3,'nav_menu_item','',0),(91,1,'2018-03-29 08:10:30','2018-03-29 02:40:30',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','91','','','2018-03-29 08:10:30','2018-03-29 02:40:30','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=91',4,'nav_menu_item','',0),(92,1,'2018-03-29 08:10:30','2018-03-29 02:40:30',' ','','','publish','closed','closed','','92','','','2018-03-29 08:10:30','2018-03-29 02:40:30','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=92',5,'nav_menu_item','',0),(93,1,'2018-03-29 08:33:08','2018-03-29 03:03:08','Hello {{NAME}},\r\n\r\nWe have published a new blog article on our website : {{POSTTITLE}}\r\n{{POSTIMAGE}}\r\n\r\nYou can view it from this link : {{POSTLINK}}\r\n\r\nThanks & Regards,\r\nAdmin\r\n\r\nYou received this email because in the past you have provided us your email address : {{EMAIL}} to receive notifications when new updates are posted.','New Post Published - {{POSTTITLE}}','','publish','closed','closed','','new-post-published-posttitle',''