t string to help spam detection.</p><p>An anonymized string created from your email address (also called a hash) may be provided to the Gravatar service to see if you are using it. The Gravatar service privacy policy is available here: https://automattic.com/privacy/. After approval of your comment, your profile picture is visible to the public in the context of your comment.</p><h3>Media</h3><p>If you upload images to the website, you should avoid uploading images with embedded location data (EXIF GPS) included. Visitors to the website can download and extract any location data from images on the website.</p><h3>Contact forms</h3><h3>Cookies</h3><p>If you leave a comment on our site you may opt-in to saving your name, email address and website in cookies. These are for your convenience so that you do not have to fill in your details again when you leave another comment. These cookies will last for one year.</p><p>If you have an account and you log in to this site, we will set a temporary cookie to determine if your browser accepts cookies. This cookie contains no personal data and is discarded when you close your browser.</p><p>When you log in, we will also set up several cookies to save your login information and your screen display choices. Login cookies last for two days, and screen options cookies last for a year. If you select &quot;Remember Me&quot;, your login will persist for two weeks. If you log out of your account, the login cookies will be removed.</p><p>If you edit or publish an article, an additional cookie will be saved in your browser. This cookie includes no personal data and simply indicates the post ID of the article you just edited. It expires after 1 day.</p><h3>Embedded content from other websites</h3><p>Articles on this site may include embedded content (e.g. videos, images, articles, etc.). Embedded content from other websites behaves in the exact same way as if the visitor has visited the other website.</p><p>These websites may collect data about you, use cookies, embed additional third-party tracking, and monitor your interaction with that embedded content, including tracking your interaction with the embedded content if you have an account and are logged in to that website.</p><h3>Analytics</h3><h2>Who we share your data with</h2><h2>How long we retain your data</h2><p>If you leave a comment, the comment and its metadata are retained indefinitely. This is so we can recognize and approve any follow-up comments automatically instead of holding them in a moderation queue.</p><p>For users that register on our website (if any), we also store the personal information they provide in their user profile. All users can see, edit, or delete their personal information at any time (except they cannot change their username). Website administrators can also see and edit that information.</p><h2>What rights you have over your data</h2><p>If you have an account on this site, or have left comments, you can request to receive an exported file of the personal data we hold about you, including any data you have provided to us. You can also request that we erase any personal data we hold about you. This does not include any data we are obliged to keep for administrative, legal, or security purposes.</p><h2>Where we send your data</h2><p>Visitor comments may be checked through an automated spam detection service.</p><h2>Your contact information</h2><h2>Additional information</h2><h3>How we protect your data</h3><h3>What data breach procedures we have in place</h3><h3>What third parties we receive data from</h3><h3>What automated decision making and/or profiling we do with user data</h3><h3>Industry regulatory disclosure requirements</h3>','Privacy Policy','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2019-02-10 12:06:50','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?page_id=210',0,'page','',0),(212,1,'2019-02-10 16:06:57','2019-02-10 10:36:57','','doctor','','inherit','open','closed','','doctor','','','2019-02-10 16:06:57','2019-02-10 10:36:57','',10,'http://hariramhospital.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/doctor.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(213,1,'2019-02-10 16:33:47','2019-02-10 11:03:47','<h2>Radiology USG X-ray CT Scan</h2>\nThe department of radiology has all the services available related to it. A full range of services related to USG, X-RAY and CT scan is present in our hospital. The technologically advanced medical state-of-art machines make us the best to provide a proper diagnostic output. This department has extremely skilled radiologists and technicians who help you in every step. The dedication to offer services 24x7 is their top most goals. We aspire to push the boundaries in the radiology section and imaging through different kind of research activities.\n<ul>\n 	<li>USG- USG is an imaging technique for various conditions. An abdominal ultrasound is done to look for any diseases that may have affected the liver, kidney, pancreas and gallbladder. Generally, ultrasound is done for determining the problems in the muscles, tendons, blood vessels, joints and internal organs as mentioned previously. The aim is to find the source of the disease or to eliminate any pathology. It is used on pregnant women by using the ultrasound. This is practiced widely around the world.</li>\n 	<li>X-Ray- This is form electromagnetic radiation. Itâ€™s usually used to detect broken bones. But there are several other reasons to use it as well like chest x-rays are done to detect pneumonia or mammograms are done to determine breast cancer.</li>\n 	<li>CT Scan (Computerized Tomography)- A series of x-rays are taken from different angles and in great details. The computer processes cross sectional images of the soft tissues and bones inside the body. The result of the images can be analyzed like a one cuts a single slice of bread from its loaf. The analysis of each image is done in great detail. If required, additional visualization to view the body from another angle is also done. In some situations, CT scan is combined with 3D imaging systems. It provides more insight about the body than a normal plain x-ray. There are several uses of a CT scan in hospitals/clinics. Many use it particularly to find out about any sort of internal injury from an accident or other traumas, as soon as possible. It is used to picture almost all parts of a human body.</li>\n</ul>\nAll our facilities are up to date and sufficient for patients. A prior appointment is all they need to take for the exam. Our staff is very qualified to assess and conduct these exams seamlessly.','Radiology USG X-Ray CT Scan','','inherit','closed','closed','','81-autosave-v1','','','2019-02-10 16:33:47','2019-02-10 11:03:47','',81,'http://hariramhospital.com/81-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(215,1,'2019-02-10 16:37:42','2019-02-10 11:07:42','Radiology-USG-X-ray-CT-Scan','Radiology-USG-X-ray-CT-Scan','','inherit','open','closed','','radiology-usg-x-ray-ct-scan-2','','','2019-02-10 16:37:54','2019-02-10 11:07:54','',81,'http://hariramhospital.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Radiology-USG-X-ray-CT-Scan.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(216,1,'2019-02-10 16:54:28','2019-02-10 11:24:28','','Vascular-Surgery','','inherit','open','closed','','vascular-surgery-2','','','2019-02-10 16:54:33','2019-02-10 11:24:33','',85,'http://hariramhospital.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Vascular-Surgery.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(217,1,'2019-02-10 16:58:15','2019-02-10 11:28:15','','leaser-treatment','','inherit','open','closed','','leaser-treatment','','','2019-02-10 16:58:20','2019-02-10 11:28:20','',82,'http://hariramhospital.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/leaser-treatment.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(218,1,'2019-02-10 17:02:22','2019-02-10 11:32:22','','Pulmonary-Department','','inherit','open','closed','','pulmonary-department-2','','','2019-02-10 17:02:27','2019-02-10 11:32:27','',86,'http://hariramhospital.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Pulmonary-Department.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(219,1,'2019-02-10 17:06:50','2019-02-10 11:36:50','','Sports-Injuries-Management','','inherit','open','closed','','sports-injuries-management-2','','','2019-02-10 17:06:56','2019-02-10 11:36:56','',83,'http://hariramhospital.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/03/Sports-Injuries-Management.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(220,1,'2019-02-10 21:01:00','2019-02-10 15:31:00','','hariram','','inherit','open','closed','','hariram','','','2019-02-10 21:01:10','2019-02-10 15:31:10','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/02/hariram.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(228,1,'2019-05-05 21:35:08','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','closed','closed','','','','','2019-05-05 21:35:08','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?post_type=gallery&p=228',0,'gallery','',0),(229,1,'2019-05-05 21:35:31','2019-05-05 16:05:31','','Hari-Ram-Hospital-Image','','inherit','open','closed','','hari-ram-hospital-image','','','2019-05-05 21:35:31','2019-05-05 16:05:31','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/Hari-Ram-Hospital-Image.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(230,1,'2019-05-05 22:02:47','2019-05-05 16:32:47','','doctor-patient','','inherit','open','closed','','doctor-patient','','','2019-05-05 22:05:49','2019-05-05 16:35:49','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/doctor-patient.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(231,1,'2019-05-05 22:16:09','2019-05-05 16:46:09','','hari-ram-hospital','','inherit','open','closed','','hari-ram-hospital','','','2019-05-05 22:16:09','2019-05-05 16:46:09','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/05/hari-ram-hospital.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(232,1,'2019-05-05 22:29:42','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2019-05-05 22:29:42','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://hariramhospital.com/?p=232',0,'post','',0);
